Description: Pregnant fifteen-year-old orphan Cecilia is sent to Ida's secluded mansion to hide pregnancy. Ida and maid Alma provide Cecilia maternal care, forming bond. Their relationship tested as Cecilia's childbirth nears.

Title: Dead Mail
Description: An ominous help note finds its way to a 1980s post office, connecting a dead letter investigator to a kidnapped keyboard technician.

Title: The Demon Disorder
Description: Tells the story of Graham, Jake and Phillip Reilly and their deceased father. Their pasts collide when a family secret is discovered, leading their father's garage to become the site of revenge from beyond the grave.

Title: Garudan
Description: Sokkan, the trusted confidant of childhood friends Aadhi and Karuna.But when his loyalty and self respect is put into test, which would he choose?

Title: ZEF: The Story of Die Antwoord
Description: The story of the controversial South African band Die Antwoord. Tracing them from their humble beginnings to global phenomenon. Like their music the documentary is shocking, provocative, highly creative and strangely funny.

Title: Stormy
Description: Behind the curtain with Stormy Daniels as she shares her story. The film follows her reinventing herself while grappling with events from 5 years earlier that made her an unlikely American icon.

Title: Sicilian Letters
Description: A time during Cosa Nostra boss Matteo Messina Denaro's three decades as a fugitive from Italian justice, when he was at the peak of his nefarious powers.

Title: The Lockdown
Description: Siblings Charlie and Jack are trapped in Myanmar's toughest prison and accused of a crime they didn't commit. Forced into televised fights against other inmates, they must work together and fight for their freedom.

Title: Bila Esok Ibu Tiada
Description: The story of 4 children who are starting to get busy with their own lives. Small problems always become big conflicts. Their mother, whose heart is broken, is confused about what to do. She just misses the laughter and harmony like before.

Title: Alpha.
Description: Rein, snowboard teacher, works in the Alps. Receives a visit from Father Gijs from the Netherlands. The two venture into the snow-capped mountains where they clash both with each other and with the merciless nature that surrounds them.

Title: God & Country
Description: Looks at the implications of Christian Nationalism and how it distorts not only the constitutional republic, but Christianity itself.

Title: The Death That Awaits
Description: A drifter searching for answers to a mystery from her past takes on a job looking after a sick teen who is undergoing a mysterious transformation her family will do anything to stop.

Title: Init
Description: When a young barrio lass moves in to the city to study, she lives in a boarding house with other college students. Unknown to them, behind her shy and timid personality is a woman with insatiable hunger for sex.

Title: Run Baby Run
Description: A young woman has to run for her life.

Title: London Calling
Description: After fleeing the UK from a job gone wrong, a down on his luck hitman is forced to babysit the son of his new crime boss and show him how to become a man.

Title: Vaazha: Biopic of a Billion Boys
Description: Four friends deemed 'losers' face immense pressure from parents and society upon entering adulthood. Their emotional tale sees them embark on a journey of self-discovery and acceptance, where love ultimately triumphs over judgment.

Title: The Paradise of Thorns
Description: Unmarried gay couple builds home, durian farm together. After one partner's accidental death, his family seizes assets due to lack of legal marriage recognition. Surviving partner fights to reclaim their shared property and life's work.

Title: 18×2 Beyond Youthful Days
Description: Ami, a Japanese backpacker, and Jimmy work together at a KTV. They bond over work and adventures, but Ami leaves suddenly. Eighteen years later, Jimmy finds a postcard from Ami, sparking a journey to Japan to find closure and reconnect.

Title: Frida
Description: A raw and magical journey into the life of iconic artist Frida Kahlo, told through her own words from diaries, letters, essays, and interviews. Vividly brought to life with lyrical animation inspired by her unforgettable artwork.

Title: Beyond the Rush
Description: Working undercover to expose a corrupt judge, an investigative journalist confronts his secret past to reconcile his mother's mental illness and must choose between addiction, obsession and the past, or love, redemption and the future.

Title: Marco
Description: Exposing the lie of Enric Marco, a Spanish trade unionist who falsely claimed surviving Nazi concentration camps, serving as president of a Holocaust survivors' group.

Title: Swargam
Description: In the bustling city, two families live parallel lives, separated by wealth and social status. As the two families navigate their lives, they face challenges and triumphs.

Title: A Christmas Storm
Description: After learning that all her immediate family members have separate plans for the upcoming Christmas, a single mother enlists her sister to help persuade them to spend Christmas Eve together.

Title: Uhaw
Description: A wife learns that her husband who's in coma had an affair. She confronts the other woman but instead finds solace in her. She then realizes she's falling for her husband's mistress.

Title: The Friendly
Description: Military medic Curtis gets injured, returns home with dog Friendly who saved him. Curtis and Friendly adjust to civilian life. Curtis falls in love with nurse Sophia, who has a child.

Title: The Girl Who Wasn't Dead
Description: 15-year-old Erica vanishes, believed a victim of a serial killer, but emerges at her murder trial 3 years later, having run away to live secretly with her older boyfriend near her mother's home, banned from seeing him.

Title: Der Spitzname
Description: Amidst the chaos of acting dreams, career obstacles, bitcoin trading, overprotective parents, job loss, and mischievous children, a couple's Alpine wedding hangs in the balance.

Title: The Greatest
Description: Inhibited by his conventional life, a man named Jay is forced to confront his darkest secret when having to choose between a life of normality and authenticity.

Title: Johatsu: Into Thin Air
Description: Disillusioned individuals in Japan vanish to start anew, aided by firms providing new identities. It delves into the turmoil of those who disappear and the loved ones grappling with their absence, exploring reconciliation attempts.

Title: Kabitan
Description: Alice, a depressed mistress, forms a deep emotional and sexual bond with Mika, her neighbor, who is also a mistress. Then, the inevitable happens, they fall for each other.

Title: Katas
Description: Carmina works as a maid in a mansion and soon learns about the dirty secret of their masters, Alex and Grace.

Title: Steal Her Breath
Description: Virtuoso thief Laura faces her ultimate challenge: outmaneuvering relentless policewoman Maxine in a dangerous, passionate cat-and-mouse game, while a sadistic killer marks them for death.

Title: Eat the Night
Description: Young drug dealer Pablo and his sister Appoline bond over an online game called Darknoon. Pablo falls for Night, neglecting his sister. While Appoline finishes the game, Pablo and Night become embroiled in a dangerous gang conflict.

Title: 12 to Midnight
Description: A detective, despondent after the murder of his wife and forced to resign, is brought back to the force when a serial killer appears to be taunting him and turns out to be superhuman.

Title: Frka
Description: After messing up a job for the local drug dealer, Nika is presented with an ultimatum that takes her and her friends on a no-holds-barred race against time in a night that will test all of their limits.

Title: Dear Kelly
Description: Filmmaker Andrew Callaghan investigates about the life of Kelly Johnson, a participant at a 2021 White Lives Matter rally in Huntington Beach, California, delving into Johnson's background and beliefs.

Title: Intercepted
Description: Destruction in Ukraine war shown through lengthy tableaux. Soldiers' phone calls to families reveal parallel world. Sound and image confront one another.

Title: The Naughty List of Mr. Scrooge
Description: Former college friends reunite 10 years after a tragedy during a production of A Christmas Carol. Gathering at a winter chalet, they are stalked and killed one by one by someone dressed as a terrifying Ebenezer Scrooge.

Title: Succubus
Description: A group of young people arrives to a remote village where they encounter an ancient spirit - a succubus - that can take human disguise. It feeds on one's deepest fears and brings out the darkest side in people.

Title: Meet the Barbarians
Description: Brittany's Town has unanimously decided to accept Ukrainian refugees in exchange for government subsidies. However, instead of seeing Ukrainians arrive, they now see Syrian migrants, which has caused some conflicts.

Title: I Am: Celine Dion
Description: A raw and honest behind-the-scenes look at the iconic superstar's struggle with Stiff Person Syndrome, a life-altering illness.

Title: All the Wrong Ingredients
Description: Desperate to win a high-stakes dessert contest, chef Ben unintentionally cooks up an imaginary friend to help him reinvent the meaning of delicious. But what happens when his ambition becomes a monster?

Title: Lucky Winners
Description: After winning the lottery, the happy winners see their lives change into a nightmare.

Title: Prom Dates
Description: Jess and Hannah, at 13 years old made a pact to have the perfect prom, only 24 hours before the big event, everything is ruined when they break up with their dates. Now they have one night to find new dates and make the fantasy comes true.

Title: A Traveler's Needs
Description: A French woman drinks makgeolli in Korea after losing her means of income, then teaches French to two Korean women.

Title: Baki Hanma VS Kengan Ashura
Description: It's the ultimate showdown. The toughest fighters from "Baki Hanma" and "Kengan Ashura" clash in this unprecedented, hard-hitting martial arts crossover.

Title: Corina
Description: Corina, a 20-year-old housebound woman, accidentally compromises her publishing company's famous book saga. To save her job and the company, she must overcome her fears and, aided by Carlos, embark on a journey to find a mysterious writer.

Title: Mission: Cross
Description: In the ultimate test of marriage, an agent-turned-househusband gets tangled in a perilous mission with his detective wife, who's clueless about his past.

Title: Pepe
Description: A voice that claims to be from a hippopotamus. A voice that doesn't understand the perception of time. Pepe, the first and last hippo killed in the Americas, tells his story with the overwhelming orality of these towns.

Title: Festival of the Living Dead
Description: While attending a festival to commemorate the original zombie attack, Ash and her friends encounter the living dead and must fight back or be devoured.

Title: Ek Daav Bhootacha
Description: Madan, a man gifted with the power to see ghosts, faces isolation and mockery. Smitten with Madhumati, his shyness prevents him from professing his love. A ghost named Shashikant strikes a deal.

Title: Layla
Description: When Layla, a struggling Arab drag queen, falls in love for the first time, they lose and find themselves in a transformative relationship that tests who they really are.

Title: Aliens Expanded
Description: An in-depth and innovative documentary that explores the story behind James Cameron's beloved sci-fi epic Aliens (1986) and its incredible impact.

Title: Consumed
Description: A married couple, Jay and Beth taking a celebratory camping trip a year after Beth's cancer remission but they find themselves trapped between a wild madman and a skin stealing monster.

Title: IVE: The 1st World Tour in Cinema
Description: K-pop sensation IVE brings their first world tour "SHOW WHAT I HAVE" to theaters. Seoul encore featuring hit performances, member interviews, and backstage moments from their global journey.

Title: Hide N Seek
Description: Vaishnavi, a determined investigator, discovers a disturbing link between multiple murders, taking her on a dangerous quest to unveil a dark conspiracy in this gripping Indian crime drama.

Title: Naples to New York
Description: Follows two Neapolitan kids as they journey to New York to escape Italy's early postwar poverty.

Title: The Holiday Junkie
Description: Follows Andie, who runs a decorating company with her mother. After her mother's passing, Andie navigates her first Christmas alone while trying to find love.

Title: Martin
Description: A journey of a man discovering himself, finding love and fighting for his motherland. Can he hold the fort on all three gates?

Title: Sharp Corner
Description: A dedicated family man becomes obsessed with saving the lives of the car accident victims on the sharp corner in front of his house - an obsession that could cost him everything.

Title: Love at 39 Degrees
Description: Fatih and Kumru, a lawyer from different cities, team up for a case involving a cheating spouse. They spend 8 hours racing around Izmir gathering evidence, unexpectedly altering their plans and lives.

Title: Becoming Hitchcock: The Legacy of Blackmail
Description: Exploring Hitchcock's iconic style through his early film "Blackmail," an insight into the director's emerging techniques and themes during the transition to talkies, showcasing elements that would define his later masterpieces.

Title: Planet B
Description: France, 2039. One night, a group of activists pursued by the state vanish without a trace. Julia Bombarth is one of them. When she awakens, she finds herself trapped in an entirely unfamiliar world: PLANET B.

Title: Marry Christmas
Description: After finding love, the Wright Brothers (Joey and Matthew Lawrence) unwittingly schedule weddings for the same day. A sibling rivalry ensues for the right to wed their brides on Christmas.

Title: On Falling
Description: The story focuses on Aurora, a Portuguese worker in a Scottish warehouse, navigating loneliness and alienation in an algorithm-driven gig economy as she seeks meaning and connection amidst solitude and workplace confines.

Title: National Theatre Live: Vanya
Description: Andrew Scott brings multiple characters to life in Chekhov's Uncle Vanya, filmed live in West End, London. Hopes, dreams, and regrets are thrust into sharp focus in this one-man adaptation which explores the complexities of human emotions.

Title: Torch Song
Description: An eccentric former pop singer visits her estranged half-brother and turns his life upside down when she finds a muse in his girlfriend.

Title: Pimpinero: Blood and Oil
Description: In the treacherous desert along the Colombia-Venezuela border, gasoline smugglers known as "pimpineros" risk their lives transporting illegal fuel across the harsh landscape.

Title: Merry Christmas
Description: Two strangers meet on a fateful Christmas Eve. A night of delirious romance turns into a nightmare. Revealing anything more would be a crime.

Title: Bade Miyan Chote Miyan
Description: Two elite soldiers with troubled pasts are enlisted for a daring mission when a deadly masked villain threatens India's defenses.

Title: Wake
Description: Desperate for a lead role in a Hollywood remake, a struggling actress tracks down the lead of the original film who's now a mysterious recluse. Strange occurrences quickly turn the meeting into a nightmare.

Title: Haikyu!! The Dumpster Battle
Description: Despite a strong field, the Karasuno High volleyball team advances past the preliminary round of the Harutaka tournament in Miyagi prefecture to reach the third round.

Title: Single Car Crashes
Description: Ten years after a tragic accident, a man tries putting his life back together when his ex-girlfriend comes back into town.

Title: Noah's Ark
Description: Tom and Vini are two bohemian mice who stow away on Noah's Ark. They must use their musical talents to enter a competition and help maintain peace among the animals.

Title: Escape
Description: A young man who wants to live in prison and will do whatever it takes to get there, raising questions such as if those who care about him will get to stop him from committing increasingly serious crimes.

Title: Oye Bhole Oye
Description: Bhola's quest for work in the city leads him to Aveera, a rich woman drawn to his simple life. But their romance faces trouble when Bhola must save his village.

Title: Magic Beach
Description: Magic Beach, based on Alison Lester's book, features nine children and a dog bringing their imaginative imaginations to life.

Title: Double Blended
Description: Two remarried couples, connected by their past marriages, navigate life as a harmonious blended family until a revelation threatens to unravel their carefully balanced relationships.

Title: Xiong Shi Shao Nian 2
Description: A Juan, an unknown person who came to Shanghai to work, agreed to participate in the "Shanghai Fight Night" martial arts competition on behalf of the declining Chuanwu Boxing Gym in order to make money to treat his father's illness.

Title: Handsome Guys
Description: Self-proclaimed tough guys 'Jae-pil' and 'Sang-gu' move into their dream European-style house. When unwanted visitors arrive, awakening an evil spirit hitherto sealed in the basement, a dark aura begins to envelop the house.

Title: Dhoom Dhaam
Description: It is an unusual mix of two love stories: 'Father and Son' and 'Son and a Beautiful girl.

Title: Ullozhukku
Description: A family's attempt to bury a loved one is thwarted by floodwaters, forcing them to confront long-buried secrets and lies that threaten their unity.

Title: Audrey's Children
Description: 1969. Dr. Audrey Evans joins world-renowned children's hospital and battles sexism, medical conventions, and the subterfuge of her peers to develop revolutionary treatments and purchase the first Ronald McDonald House, impacting millions.

Title: Sicilian Holiday
Description: It folllows Mia and Nino. Mia is trying to find an escape from her unfulfilling life. Nino is a sculptor in his mid-thirties who comes to Mia's aid. Their relationship becomes complicated by the arrival of Nino's brother Phil.

Title: The Traveller
Description: Based on the popular Chinese graphic novel The Outcast.

Title: John Cranko
Description: Joachim Lang's biopic about the brilliant dancer and choreographer John Cranko, who left the Royal Ballet in London and found fame in Stuttgart as its great dance creator.

Title: Yudhra
Description: A young man consumed by vengeance, Yudhra infiltrates a ruthless cartel to avenge his murdered parents, only to discover a dark truth about his past that will test his limits.

Title: Little Wing
Description: A 13-year-old girl is dragged into the world of pigeon racing as she deals with her parents' divorce and the impending loss of her home.

Title: Hauntology
Description: An older sister takes her fearless runaway sibling on a road trip, to share the most chilling tales surrounding their hometown.

Title: Bhaje Vaayu Vegam
Description: To pay for surgery for his father, an aspiring cricketer makes a big bet. When the bookie cheats him, he retaliates - and gets caught in a crime web.

Title: Eks
Description: Three compelling stories in one erotic experience. Yen Durano plays three different women in three titillating stories.

Title: Chhava
Description: Set in the storied Apshinge Military Village in Maharashtra, 'Chhava' offers an intimate glimpse into the lives of families bound by centuries of military service, from the reign of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj to today.

Title: People in the Walls
Description: Rachel is introduced to a viral craze of allowing people who living the walls out into the world. This ends up badly and when her parents don't believe her two kids from her school do as they attempt to fight back against these creatures.

Title: Nahir
Description: The story of the crime that paralyzed an entire country, the teenager who murdered her boyfriend under circumstances that are not yet known for certain. Based on a real event.

Title: The Magician's Raincoat
Description: Three kids discover a magical raincoat that transports them into the body of its owner, a cursed magician. With a scorned witch hot on their trail, they must solve the mystery of the raincoat and break its curse before it's too late.

Title: Storm Crashers
Description: 11-year-old Alfonso, heir of Don Quixote, and his 3 imaginary and musical rabbits join Pancho and Victoria, to save their beloved town of La Mancha from a huge storm.

Title: The Wingwalker
Description: A young widower is deported as his daughter is scheduled for a heart transplant, this will lead him to orchestrate the boldest border crossing plan in history.

Title: Fluxx
Description: "FLUXX" is a mind-bending multi-genre film centered on an actress determined to rescue her famous missing husband, despite unable to willingly leave her Hollywood Hills home-trapped in a reality warping time, memory, and her own identity.

Title: Waarom Wettelen
Description: The death of Christine and the choice to bury her in Acanda lead to the unraveling of unexpected family secrets on the journey to her final resting place.

Title: The Corpse Washer
Description: Lela, a mortician, grapples with uncovering the truth behind her mother's mysterious deaths while haunted by spirits and burdened by the weight of untold secrets.

Title: My First Film
Description: Follow a young filmmaker, as she recounts the story of struggling to make her first feature. Fact bleeding into fiction, and past, present, and future converging to create a modern myth that redefines the very act of creation.

Title: The Honey Trap
Description: Documentary chronicling the story of Denis Cuspert, aka Deso Dogg, and his journey from infamous German rapper to ISIS recruiter.

Title: Fasal
Description: A farmer's story highlighting the challenges and hardships he faces while navigating the market value of his crops.

Title: Happyend
Description: In near-future Tokyo, the threat of a catastrophic quake looms. Two friends prank their principal before graduation, leading to school surveillance installation.

Title: Shadow Land
Description: Haunted by relentless nightmares foretelling his untimely demise, Former President Robert Wainwright summons his past psychiatrist to his upstate residence who discovers the threat may be more real than imagined.

Title: Taken from Rio Bravo
Description: In 1874 Texas, two friends and an Indian scout rescue kidnapped women from sadistic traffickers near the Mexican border.

Title: Bambi: A Tale of Life in the Woods
Description: From birth, Bambi is close to his mother, learning survival in the forest. He makes friends, but after hunters kill his mother, he becomes an orphan. With guidance from his father, Bambi learns to navigate life's dangers and matures.

Title: Vijay 69
Description: A quirky slice-of-life film where a man decides to compete in a triathlon contest at the age of 69. It stars Anupam Kher in the lead role and is written and directed by Akshay Roy.

Title: Amy Winehouse
Description: Amy Winehouse, an English singer-songwriter known for her distinct vocals and musical blend, rose to fame but battled substance abuse and mental health struggles. she passed away in 2011 at age 27, leaving a powerful musical legacy.

Title: Gaami
Description: Shankar, an amnesiac Aghori who suffers from the fear of touch, goes on a dangerous Himalayan trail in search of a mythical cure for his condition. What happens when his past uncovers the way for him?

Title: Nuked
Description: A group of friends gets together for a cannabis-infused, technology free, dinner party only to learn a bomb is headed right for them.

Title: The Honest Candidate
Description: A former idealist leader turned corrupt politician is cursed by his grandmother on the eve of the presidential elections, forcing him to be honest.

Title: Devil's Knight
Description: In the realm of Veroka, an elite group of global monster hunters is summoned by King Samuel to vanquish the ancient Bone Devil, whose reign of terror threatens the Kingdom of Remény.

Title: Dilig
Description: About to get married to an old, wealthy businessman, Resa enlists the help of gardener Otso to seduce her fiancé's daughter, Katelyn, and record his sexploits with her in order to get her disowned.

Title: Lethal Love Affair
Description: A woman finds herself in a never-ending nightmare after she breaks things off with her girlfriend, who isn't quite ready to let her go.

Title: Return of the King: The Fall and Rise of Elvis Presley
Description: He had one chance to show the world he was still the King of Rock 'n' Roll. Discover the story behind Elvis Presley's triumphant '68 comeback special.

Title: Rap World
Description: In 2009, four friends living in Tobyhanna, Pennsylvania document their attempt to record a rap album over the course of one eventful night.

Title: Brewster's Millions: Christmas
Description: Follows Morgan Brewster's quest to inherit her uncle's fortune before Christmas. Amid holiday chaos, she discovers love, faith, and family's importance through giving.

Title: La pie voleuse
Description: Maria is no longer young and helps people who are even older than she is. Struggling to make ends meet, she refuses to accept her precarious situation and occasionally steals a few euros from the kind souls she cares for with extreme devotion--who, in return, adore her.

Title: Jim Henson: Idea Man
Description: This documentary features interviews of fans of Jim Henson's work, interspersed with footage from his works, including Wilkins and Wontkins Commercials, that were previously lost.

Title: Terrornet
Description: Follows David Edison, a cam-girl obsessed I.T. guy, as he becomes possessed by Asmodeus, the demon of lust, who begins harassing women online while destroying David's life.

Title: To Dye For: The Documentary
Description: After discovering that their child has a life-altering sensitivity to synthetic dyes, parents and first-time filmmakers Brandon and Whitney Cawood are documenting their journey to unravel the impacts of synthetic dyes.

Title: She Came Back
Description: The terrifying journey of Charley who, after a near-death experience, is haunted by her relationship with her deceased mother.

Title: Atatürk II: 1881-1919
Description: After proving himself at Gallipoli in 1915, Mustafa Kemal began his journey, facing major battles against Russians on the eastern front and British in Syria, becoming the only undefeated Ottoman officer in WW1.

Title: Made in England: The Films of Powell and Pressburger
Description: Features rare archival material from the personal collections of Powell, Pressburger and Scorsese.

Title: Vindication Swim
Description: The inspirational story of Mercedes Gleitze, the first British woman to swim the English Channel and her battle against both the cold waters of the Channel and the oppressive society of 1920s England.

Title: My Nanny Stole My Life
Description: A new mother begins to suspect that her nanny is scheming to steal her baby and her husband.

Title: Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba - To the Hashira Training
Description: Tanjiro undergoes rigorous training with the Stone Hashira, Himejima, in his quest to become a Hashira. Meanwhile, Muzan continues to search for Nezuko and Ubuyashiki.

Title: Borderless Fog
Description: A detective is forced to confront the ghosts of her past while investigating a mysterious serial murder case along the Indonesia-Malaysia border.

Title: Disaster Holiday
Description: Dad promises an exotic vacation but mistakenly books Durban instead of Zanzibar. Chaos ensues as the family's dream trip spirals into hilarity, while dad scrambles to secure a promotion.

Title: Sci-Fi Vixens from Beyond
Description: A curious alien researcher arrives on Earth to study human behavior, becoming fascinated by the attractive space warriors and cosmic adventurers who protect our planet from otherworldly threats.

Title: Camera
Description: Follows nine-year-old Oscar, a non-verbal child who struggles to fit in, as he meets Eric, a kind repair shop owner, and become unlikely friends after being brought together by a damaged film format camera.

Title: Invited
Description: When a reluctant mother attends her daughter's Zoom elopement, she and the rest of the family in attendance quickly realize the groom is part of a Russian cult with deadly intentions.

Title: Drømmer
Description: Johanne documents her intense crush on her french teacher. Her mother, grandmother end up reading these intimate writings. They're both horrified by the contents but taken by the powerful writing and story. Johanne navigates romantic ideals vs reality, exploring emotions of self-discovery, love, sexuality.

Title: Bitconned
Description: In this true-crime documentary, three guys exploit the freewheeling cryptocurrency market to scam millions from investors and bankroll lavish lifestyles.

Title: Blue Lock: Episode Nagi
Description: Seishiro Nagi before he enters the titular Blue Lock facility.

Title: Norman's Rare Guitars Documentary
Description: This world-renowned institution is where legends jam, and find inspiration. This documentary chronicles the shop's unique spirit, as Norman Harris, its beloved founder, faces retirement, marking a turning point for this cultural haven.

Title: Lolo and the Kid
Description: A hustler and the child he took in routinely con the wealthy - but a life-changing opportunity could end their inseparable bond.

Title: Three Friends
Description: Joan's love fades for Victor while Alice reassures her about her own unfulfilling relationship with Eric. Unbeknownst to Alice, Eric is involved with Rebecca. Their lives spiral after Joan leaves Victor, who goes missing.

Title: Child Star
Description: Examine how some of the most well-known former child stars, such as Lovato, deconstruct the highs and lows of growing up in the spotlight and how their ascension to fame, riches, and power affects their futures.

Title: Casatoria
Description: A degenerate gambler (Liviu Pintileasa) and his two idiot friends (Mihai Bendeac and Vlad Dragulin) come up with an elaborate plan to pay down their colossal gambling debts by marrying the dysfunctional daughter of an upstart billionaire.

Title: Lunacy
Description: Six strangers receive an alluring invitation to an island retreat but find themselves trapped by a mysterious force. Improvised in Australia's Daintree Rainforest, Lunacy explores our lost connection to the environment and our true self.

Title: Phullwanti
Description: Famous dancer Phullwanti's performance at Peshwa's court faces interruption from scholar Venkat Shastri. Defending her art, she challenges him, igniting a contest between her artistic talent and his intellect.

Title: Following
Description: A mystery thriller about a real estate agent who secretly enters clients' homes and becomes obsessed with a deceptive social media influencer. The film explores themes of obsession, identity and the dark side of social media.

Title: The Invisibles
Description: A couple facing the end of marriage, when the husband starts to disappear. As he fades from existence he discovers a new world of people who have disappeared just like him.

Title: On the Run
Description: Two teen sisters learn about their family's involvement with a secret program and go on the run to escape the deadly criminals targeting their family.

Title: Guntur Kaaram
Description: Years after his mother abandons him and remarries, a man demands answers when he's asked to sign a document denying he is her son as she runs for office.

Title: Hagen
Description: A reinterpretation of the Nibelungen saga centering on Hagen von Tronje, a Viking who allies himself with the ancient gods and takes up arms against an unscrupulous ruler.

Title: Fly
Description: Over seven years, three couples involved in the extreme sport of BASE jumping test the limits of love and life itself. Risking everything for the thrill of the jump, their dedication is put to the ultimate test.

Title: The Last Redemption
Description: Epic quest pits fearless outlaw Diana and knight Tyrion against villainous Lord Roland for kingdom's survival. They unite to defeat Roland, save princess, and restore peace after uncovering truths about rebellion and kingdom's fate.

Title: The Tyrant
Description: The story of people who gather to occupy samples for different purposes after the last sample of the so-called 'Tyrant Program' disappears in a delivery accident.

Title: A '90s Christmas
Description: While celebrating her promotion alone on Christmas Eve, a workaholic lawyer is transported back to 1999 via a mysterious rideshare experience.

Title: Finding Faith
Description: Victoria, a Christian advice columnist writing under the name Faith, begins to lose her faith after a series of life events. On her journey back to God, she also finds her way back to love.

Title: She Taught Love
Description: A guy, Frank, on a self-destructive path. A girl, Mali, with an expiration date. What a perfect time to meet and fall in love.

Title: Hayao Miyazaki and the Heron
Description: A two-hour window into the heart of Hayao Miyazaki's creative process, the documentary follows six long years of work during the making of The Boy and the Heron, the latest film by the master of Japanese animation.

Title: Plastic People
Description: Scientists investigate the threat of microplastics in human bodies. Journalist visits labs and undergoes testing to find plastic in home, food and body.

Title: Breakup Season
Description: A young man brings his girlfriend to his rural Oregon hometown to introduce her to his family, only for things to go terribly wrong upon arrival.

Title: Savages
Description: In Borneo, at the edge of the tropical forest, Kéria is given a baby orangutan. With the forest under greater threat than ever, Kéria, Selaï and the little primate, Oshi, will have to face many obstacles.

Title: Friedas Fall
Description: The murder of a young woman's son sparks a pivotal moment in the fight for women's rights and political equality in early 20th century Switzerland, setting the stage for a historic court case.

Title: Hazard
Description: A young man faces hard life choices and tragedies as he attempts to break the cycle of addiction tearing his family apart.

Title: Art of Love
Description: After learning that the art thief she has been chasing is her ex-lover, an officer working for Interpol concocts a plan to catch him red-handed.

Title: Dirty Money
Description: Two detectives struggling with their own needs, succumb to temptation when handling a large amount of cash

Title: A Vintage Christmas
Description: Sparks fly when a developer, Noah (Russell) arrives in Oak Creek with plans to replace an abandoned Post Office with a modern office complex and needs to work with Tessa (Patterson) the town's historian/preservationist to compromise.

Title: Jamais sans mon psy
Description: Follow this man with severe anxiety and a behavior his therapist cannot stand deciding to kick him out of his practice and challenge him to find the woman of his dreams.

Title: Everybody Loves Jenifa
Description: Jenifa's popularity fades when a shady new neighbor, Lobster, outshines her charity work. In Ghana, Jenifa and friends face a deadly drug baron after a bag of drugs is mistakenly left in their rental.

Title: Love Switch
Description: Married couple James and Michelle, on the verge of divorce, magically switch bodies on their anniversary. Forced to experience life from each other's perspectives, they gain newfound respect and understanding, rekindling their love.

Title: Niki
Description: Follows Saint-Phalle while she is modeling and striving to be an actor. She's married and has a daughter who is two years old. They left the United States during the harsh McCarthy era and travel to France, where they briefly feel elated.

Title: Griffin in Summer
Description: Fourteen-year-old Griffin Nafly is the most ambitious playwright of his generation. But once he meets handsome twenty-five-year-old handyman Brad, his life (and play) will never be the same.

Title: Deaner '89
Description: A hilarious headbanger finally makes it after struggling for decades, revealing it was all because of a childhood incident when the dark forces of heavy metal reached out from the grave.

Title: Horny Teenagers Must Die!
Description: A group of high school graduates travel to a cabin in the woods to celebrate and party, only to be picked off one by one by a demented psychopath who kills with farm tools and sex toys.

Title: Guruvayoor Ambalanadayil
Description: A young man never wanted to marry because his girlfriend married someone else. Five years later, he was all set to get married. But a discovery about his bride's extended family forces him to reconsider? Will he marry her?

Title: Bonjour Tristesse
Description: Follows Cécile, a young woman who spends the summer in a villa in the south of France with her widowed father Raymond and his latest love interest, Elsa. Theirs is a lived-in compatibility a world of ease and languor.

Title: Spirit in the Blood
Description: After a young girl is found dead in a secluded religious mountain community, a pack of teenage girls decide to fight against the evil spirits they believe killed her by embracing their own dark nature.

Title: Children of the Cult
Description: Osho cult survivors recount the harrowing experiences they endured as children in 'Wild Wild Country' Osho communes in the 80s, exposing a systemic culture of exploitation and attempting to talk to those responsible.

Title: Turno Nocturno
Description: A young nurse with a past of family violence starts working the night shift at a small hospital, where during the night a ghost nurse materializes.

Title: Singing in My Sleep
Description: A brilliant teenage songwriter is stuck living in the shadow of her deceased Dad's music legacy when the 20-year anniversary of his debut album forces her to face his abandonment.

Title: Skywalkers: A Love Story
Description: A daring couple travels worldwide to climb the 118-story megatall skyscraper, Merdeka 118, in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, attempting a bold acrobatic stunt on the spire to salvage both their career and relationship.

Title: Landkrimi: Steirergift
Description: Thrown away like garbage, but with faint signs of life - this is how workers find the waitress Julia at a landfill site on the edge of the forest in Leoben. Despite all efforts, the young woman dies shortly afterwards. Chief Inspector Bergmann and his colleague Anni Sulmtaler learn that she was drugged with knockout drops and raped. The first suspicion falls on her ex-boyfriend Max, who did not want to accept the break-up with Julia. But his friends Leonard and Fritz, like him in a fraternity, give him - and therefore themselves - an alibi. The investigation is stalled. Julia's sister Vanessa makes a momentous decision.

Title: Nunakuzhi
Description: A young man caught in a web of lies and mistaken identities.

Title: Remnant
Description: A tragic accident, a fractured mind, a body healed by an experimental technology. A young woman becomes supernaturally linked to the horrors of her past. Haunted, hunted, harrowed, she must uncover the truth in order to be free.

Title: Unit 234
Description: After the shocking discovery of an unconscious man in a locked unit, the lone employee of a remote storage facility must fight to survive the night against a ruthless gang, dead set on retrieving their precious cargo - at any cost.

Title: The Thinking Game
Description: Chronicles visionary scientist Demis Hassabis' relentless pursuit to crack artificial general intelligence, a journey of extraordinary perseverance.

Title: Cesium Fallout
Description: In a Hong Kong recycling plant, a massive fire exposes a radiation crisis caused by illegal garbage smuggling. Government advisor, executive, and firefighters embark on a high-stakes mission to mitigate the disaster.

Title: The Casagrandes Movie
Description: After a surprise family trip to Mexico derails Ronnie Anne's birthday plans, she is determined to prove she's old enough to do her own thing - even if it means confronting an ancient preteen demigod whose angst has apocalyptic potential.

Title: Nova & Alice
Description: Nova and Alice are two contrasting artists who are reluctantly forced to go on a joint tour by their manager. The clash is inevitable - both musically and personally.

Title: L'heureuse élue
Description: Man in debt convinces driver Fiona to pose as his model fiancée to fool his wealthy family in Morocco and secure money. They spend a weekend pretending to be engaged during a family gathering.

Title: The Glassworker
Description: The life of a young glassblower in training and his relationships over the years, as his land goes through war and strife.

Title: A Christmas Castle Proposal: A Royal in Paradise 2
Description: Despite busy schedules causing distance, Olivia and Prince Alexander travel to Torovia for Christmas with his family. Clashing cultures between their families lead to various mishaps.

Title: Dead Wrong
Description: A narcissist concocts a get-rich-quick scheme that ignites a violent chain reaction and overwhelms the lives of those around him.

Title: Auron Mein Kahan Dum Tha
Description: After 20 years in prison, a man reunites with his lost love and the truth behind his crimes is revealed.

Title: Just a Farmer
Description: A newly widowed mother is left with the care of an alcoholic father-in-law and a failing farm. She is forced to forge a new path for her family, all while struggling to pick up the pieces of her life.

Title: Valentine's Town
Description: Jude works for a well-known dating service that will develop a cheesy, romantic resort in his hometown of Arrowheart. Local businesswoman Melissa has organized the town against the resort. Melissa is Jude's former high school sweetheart.

Title: My Freaky Family
Description: Betty Flood, a preteen with musical talents and magical abilities, struggles to fit in with her unconventional family. As she approaches her 13th birthday, she unravels family secrets, embracing her unique identity.

Title: Metro.... In Dino
Description: Follows stories of bittersweet relationships in a contemporary setting, exploring various aspects, hues, and moods of love.

Title: Hunting with Tigers
Description: Malik returns from Spain to learn his stepfather Serge was arrested. On trial day lawyer Iris offers Malik a deal, pull off a dangerous heist in exchange for Serge's freedom. Malik agrees and joins ex-partners of Cherif for one last job.

Title: Haunt Season
Description: A masked maniac targets cast members at a suburban Halloween haunt attraction, turning their staged injuries into gruesome real-life horrors. As the terror escalates, the lines between performance and reality blur.

Title: Bolehkah Sekali Saja Kumenangis
Description: After her brother left home, Tari struggled alone to save her mother from her abusive father. Tari, who has been traumatized since childhood decided to join a support group along with Baskara. They seek salvation by opening up their heart.

Title: Jamie Foxx: What Had Happened Was...
Description: A stand-up special with Jamie Foxx performing before an Atlanta crowd. Containing songs and anecdotes, the main topic is his time away from the limelight while undergoing a medical emergency in 2023.

Title: Bau: Artist at War
Description: The inspiring love story of Joseph Bau, artist, forger, holocaust survivor. Using his artistic skills, humor and hope in the camps, Joseph stays alive and helps hundreds to escape. Miraculously, he finds love in the midst of despair.

Title: From the River to the Sea: The Frontiers of Faith
Description: This film is an invitation to understand that the war in Israel is not just a territorial dispute in the Middle East, but a global war over two worldviews.

Title: Chateau
Description: While on a French vacation funded by odd jobs, an aspiring influencer covertly films a vlog in a reportedly haunted chateau she's been hired to clean.

Title: Stranger in the Woods
Description: Follows Olivia and her friends as they go on a vacation. After Olivia nearly drowns with a slit wrist in her bathtub after her fiancé's funeral, her friends suspect that she tried to kill herself, but she believes someone attacked her.

Title: Christmas Slasher
Description: Murderous zombie reindeer Slasher and psychotic Mr. and Mrs. Claus terrorize friends vacationing in a cabin, targeting Alita Claus and her group during Christmas break. Alita must save her friends from the holiday horrors.

Title: Sevmek Yüzünden
Description: Idil, a wedding dress designer, finds herself caught in a conflict involving her ex-boyfriend and a bride's impending marriage. As she navigates this situation, she grapples with her own past and the complexities of relationships.

Title: The Groomsmen: Second Chances
Description: Danny finds the courage to admit his romantic feelings for his best friend when he is asked to be the best man at his wedding in Greece.

Title: Jailbreak: Love on the Run
Description: When Vicky White, a highly respected corrections officer, aids the escape of a violent felon nearly twenty years her junior, it reveals an unexpected love story amidst the ensuing high-profile manhunt and media frenzy.

Title: Kiskisan
Description: Steamy tale of love, lust, and betrayal. When Adele's sister Bea returns with her girlfriend Cheska, a secret affair begins between Cheska and Adele's boyfriend, Rener, leading to a climactic ending when they're caught.

Title: Life of Belle
Description: In 2018, Annabelle Starnes went missing. York County police released surveillance footage of the home in hopes of new leads.

Title: Tears of Cem Karaca
Description: It tells the life story of Cem Karaca, the legendary name of Anatolian rock music, who has created many works.

Title: Seeds
Description: Ziggy, a Mohawk woman, gets hired as an influencer for Nature's Oath company. Her cousin calls her back to their reservation, embroiling her in a fight to preserve their people's heritage amid corporate interests.

Title: Vulgar
Description: Angelika's seemingly perfect life conceals a lack of fulfillment. While arranging her best friend's wedding, she meets Simon, her friend's daring and passionate brother who challenges Angelika's deeply held principles and life beliefs.

Title: McVeigh
Description: Army veteran Timothy McVeigh hatches a deadly plan after the Waco siege. A psychological thriller depicting the deadliest act of domestic terrorism in U.S. history.

Title: The Shamrock Spitfire
Description: The story of Irish fighter pilot Brendan "Paddy" Finucane, who at the age of just 21, became the youngest ever wing commander in the Royal Air Force, and one of its greatest and most celebrated fighter aces during World War II.

Title: Boys on Film 24: Happy Endings
Description: Let BOYS ON FILM move, inspire and uplift you with this stunning collection of 11 new gay short films, marking the final physical edition of the series.

Title: The Windigo
Description: A Native American teen resurrects an ancient demon to protect his family from meth dealers, but finds the creature's bloodlust uncontrollable, forcing the family to break the curse before becoming its next victims.

Title: Futra Days
Description: After undergoing an experimental time travel "process" that sends a man into his future, he investigates the man he has become, by engaging in a romance with his future self's girlfriend in a mind-bending reality.

Title: Butas
Description: Witness how lives of four young people who have various sexual quirks and inhibitions intertwine as they live together in a snug boarding house.

Title: Snatched a Billionaire to be My Husband
Description: Cora, once a billionaire heiress, is now bankrupt. As she struggles to support her ill mother, a cold-hearted billionaire falls for her, giving Cora a chance at reclaiming her life. They find true love, proving it transcends wealth.

Title: They Called Him Mostly Harmless
Description: A hiker found dead in Florida wilderness is identified by internet sleuths after 2 years. His identity triggers more questions as multiple hikers claim to have met him, but he never revealed his name.

Title: Chapel
Description: A man becomes a suspect in a serial murder case after waking from a coma with no recollection of who he is

Title: The Holiday Exchange
Description: Wilde must cope with vacationing as a bachelor, so he decides to swap houses on an LGBTQ app with Oliver. In their efforts to escape their woes they end up meeting two locals who set romance on fire from LA to the charming town of Brilfax.

Title: Filthy Animals
Description: Two outlaw misfits, Lars, a thrill-seeking drug enthusiast, and Freddy, a bodybuilder recently out of rehab, hunt down child sexual predators on Christmas Eve.

Title: Government Gangsters
Description: Government conspiracy to undermine President Trump and his supporters, exposing corruption, deceit, and betrayal within the system meant to protect democracy.

Title: The Magic Penguin
Description: When a beloved talking penguin named Roi is kidnapped by a couple of criminals, his home country is thrown into a tailspin. The most trusted knight in the land and his young son must join forces to rescue their fine feathered friend

Title: Top 1
Description: Azi and Dex are both vying to be their batch valedictorian but Dex is always behind Azi. He then plans to make her fall in love to be a distraction, but his plan is a double-edged sword.

Title: Soda
Description: In 1956, a seamstress arrives in a Holocaust survivor community. Rumors surface about her past as Capo. Shalom, resistance fighter, torn between attraction and duty to expose her history. Community tensions rise over her true identity.

Title: Cheaters
Description: Two strangers meet and have strong sexual connection with each other, only to find out that they're both in relationship with others. How can they sustain a relationship that started with sex and cheating?

Title: Winter in Sokcho
Description: A young Korean girl's life takes an unexpected turn when a French artist visits her country, disrupting her routine.

Title: Break
Description: Eli learns that his absent father was a Detroit pool hall legend. He journeys into the scene, and must confront the realities and danger of the game - and himself.

Title: Rob N Roll
Description: Decadent Murong Hui teams up with violent bandits after a botched robbery. A female detective pursues them as they scheme to steal a bag of money, leading to chaotic events due to betrayals and twists under the "I rob, you rob me" code.

Title: The Book of Jobs
Description: A girl raised in Silicon Valley in the shadow of Steve Jobs' successful return to Apple, and his huge influence on her imagination, her aspirations and relationships.

Title: The Last Chainsaw Massacre
Description: A group of teenagers camping in a remote town encounter a deranged killer known as The Chainsaw Man, who wears a human flesh mask and wields a blood-soaked chainsaw.

Title: Demise
Description: Caleb Castillo, a Latino landscaper, is involved in a scandal with fashion star Fiona Hernandez and is devoted to his wife Celine. They break up, and Celine reclaims her son Brody (Fiona's & caleb's), despite Caleb's promises to leave her.

Title: Rise of OnlyFans
Description: The Rise of OnlyFans is an illuminating documentary that provides a comprehensive exploration of the unprecedented growth and cultural impact of the groundbreaking platform, OnlyFans.

Title: Son's Will
Description: A post-apocalyptic tale set in the west Balkans, after a nuclear war.

Title: Intrusive
Description: A married man's forbidden encounter with his wife's friend spirals into a maze of guilt and conflicting loyalties, forcing him to navigate the aftermath of one passionate mistake.

Title: Kulong
Description: Three celibate friends seclude themselves at a resort to pen a steamy script for a competition, but struggle to write convincingly about intimacy they haven't experienced.

Title: The Charisma Killers
Description: When the old mentor of 7 killers finds out he has terminal cancer, he gives them all an opportunity at his fortune to prove themselves for one night only to exact revenge.

Title: Los domingos mueren más personas
Description: David returns to Buenos Aires from Europe for his uncle's funeral. Once there, he learns that his mother has decided to pull the plug on his comatose father. David oscillates between his past and present, as he tries to find his own place.

Title: The Promise
Description: While trapped in her car miles away, Maja must overcome her fears and go to extraordinary lengths to save her unruly nephew Mathias from a ruthless gang that has kidnapped him. Inspired by true events.

Title: Siddharth Roy
Description: Siddharth Roy Embraces logic and reason but is overwhelmed by emotions, resulting in heartache and inner turmoil.

Title: TL
Description: Brenda, a top agent in a BPO company, is always overlooked for promotion. But not this time; as she gets more than intimate with her TL. Is her long awaited position within her reach? Or did she just put herself in a bad situation?

Title: And Their Children After Them
Description: In eastern France, two teenage cousins have the summer of their lives when they paddle a purloined canoe to the far shore of a lake.

Title: Rogue Elements: A Ryan Drake Story
Description: Ryan Drake, hoping to recover an asset, must infiltrate a fortified base, his every move watched by a shadowy figure. He silently makes his way to the base and rescues the asset. Hell breaks out when the figure makes its presence known.

Title: Junction
Description: Junction addresses the modern day opioid crisis in America, and asks how did this happen, from three different points of view. The CEO of a pharmaceutical company, a doctor, and a patient.

Title: Enough for Now
Description: Siblings bake coconut cubes dessert to lure eldest brother home. Time appears frozen. Ordinary summer days become extraordinary. Joyous spirit alleviates darkness. Brothers reunite through baking shared favorite treat.

Title: Bhairathi Ranagal
Description: Bhairathi Ranagal delves into the story of Ranagal. How did he rise to such prominence? The film focuses on his origin, his journey to power, and who he was before he became the most dreaded gangster of Ronapura.

Title: DIG! XX
Description: Two rock bands, The Dandy Warhols and The Brian Jonestown Massacre, navigate fame, friendship, and fierce rivalry in a raw journey through the music industry. The 20th anniversary cut adds fresh footage and new perspectives.

Title: Death's Sonata
Description: The story of a man suffering from Schizophrenia and the psychotherapist who tries to find him with the help of his young Bi-Polar patient.

Title: The Time It Takes
Description: A deeply felt narrative of the filmmaker's time with her father. A story that's both personal and told with the necessary distance. Like a passion, a life choice and a way of being in the world.

Title: The Bunker
Description: When mysterious alien ships appear in the sky, a scientist is sealed in an underground bunker and must create a bio-weapon to stop the unknown visitors, but paranoia and isolation cause her to question the true intention of her mission.

Title: Camp Pleasant Lake
Description: A couple breathes life into a new camp on an old campsite, connecting them to a chilling past that unravels a 20-year-old mystery involving a missing young girl. As eerie events unfold, they must confront forces tied to a brutal crime.

Title: Mascarpone: The Rainbow Cake
Description: After three years, Antonio and Luca are reunited. Antonio, a successful pastry chef, still has feelings for Luca, who is now engaged to Tancredi. Antonio is convinced that the past has come back to help them.

Title: Empire Waist
Description: Follows a group of teens learning to love their bodies through inclusive fashion design and friendship.

Title: Harry Potter and the Stone
Description: Harry Potter, an eleven-year-old orphan, discovers that he is a wizard and is invited to study at Hogwarts. Even as he escapes a dreary life and enters a world of magic, he finds trouble awaiting him.

Title: The Snow Sister
Description: A young boy named Julian, whose Christmas Eve birthday turns sad with the death of his sister sends his household into mourning and it isn't until he meets Christmas-loving Hedwig that he begins to believe in Christmas again.

Title: Boléro
Description: In 1928 Paris, choreographer Ida Rubinstein commissions Maurice Ravel to compose the music for her next ballet. Facing a crisis of inspiration, the composer revisits his life and dedicates himself to create a universal masterpiece, Bolero.

Title: Peacock
Description: Matthias masters impersonating roles for hire: cultured boyfriend, perfect son, sparring partner. Professionally adept at pretending daily, his true challenge lies in being himself.

Title: Donselya
Description: An 18-year-old virgin, Iris, enters a marriage of convenience with wealthy widower Joaquin for financial gain. However, the discovery of her deceit regarding her purity leads to a disastrous honeymoon.

Title: Passport to Love
Description: A successful international travel writer, Nicole, has scored a dream seaside rental to research her newest vacation article only to discover it has accidentally been booked also by Kade, a marketing rep for a competing travel magazine.

Title: Apollo 13: Survival
Description: In April 1970, NASA faced the greatest crisis in its history; three astronauts halfway to the moon on a spacecraft that had suffered a catastrophic explosion.

Title: Escape from the 21st Century
Description: The story follows three friends who discover they have the power to travel back and forth 20 years with a sneeze. However, the future is not as good as they hoped, and they need to take on the responsibility of saving the world.

Title: Por donde pasa el silencio
Description: Antonio (30) returns to his home after a long absence. He then discovers that his family is on the brink of falling apart because of his fraternal twin, who suffers from severe back malformation. Now, he is going to have to face him.

Title: The Hangman
Description: Troubled father Leon takes son camping in Appalachia. Local cult summons evil Hangman demon. Son goes missing. Leon must confront cult, monster to find him amid rising body count.

Title: Alles Fifty Fifty
Description: A divorced couple takes a trip to Italy for a family vacation with their young son and her new boyfriend.

Title: Flight 404
Description: Days before traveling to Mecca for HAJJ, Ghada is faced with an emergency and needs a large sum of money. She must return to a tainted past and keep it from consuming her.

Title: White Snake: Afloat
Description: Xiaobai finally found Xu Xian, the reincarnation of Axuan, after 500 years, the two met on the Broken Bridge. Xiaobai and sister hid in the streets and alleys, started a lively life in human world with him and his brother-in-law Li Gongfu.

Title: Footage
Description: A found footage thriller surrounding the story of a curious couple.

Title: The Ghost Trap
Description: A young lobsterman is forced to choose between right and wrong when his girlfriend suffers a traumatic head injury and a rival lobstering family sabotages his gear.

Title: Cellphone
Description: Wynne, who is suffering PTSD from the death of her fiancé, starts seeing disturbing images on her cell phone about her future. If she doesn't figure them out in time, she will die.

Title: Shepherds
Description: A young Montreal advertising executive, converted to a Provençal shepherd, has various misadventures with a civil servant who has cavalierly quit her job.

Title: Vil & Misérable
Description: In a world where books and cars share a sales floor, a misanthropic and immortal bookselling demon is forced to team up with a young, enthusiastic human assistant to save his bookstore.

Title: Doin' It
Description: An Indian-American virgin gets a job teaching high school sex ed.

Title: Time Travel Is Dangerous
Description: Best friends Ruth and Megan run a vintage shop in Muswell Hill. Stumbling across a time machine, they embark on trips to the past to stock their shop with no idea of the irreparable damage they're causing to the fabric of the universe.

Title: Gloria!
Description: It re-imagines the world of classical music on more equal standing in a Neoclassical-era Venice.

Title: Toofan
Description: Follows a born killer who rises to power and becomes the biggest toofan

Title: Reading Lolita in Tehran
Description: The autobiographical story of a fearless teacher who secretly gathers seven of her female students to read forbidden Western classics in revolutionary Iran.

Title: Bee Hive
Description: Three women on hard times look to deal drugs for a local kingpin.

Title: Phir Aayi Hasseen Dillruba
Description: While evading the cops in Agra, Rani and Rishu scheme to run away together. But when their plans go awry, Rani asks a mild-mannered admirer for help.

Title: Nosferatu: The Real Story
Description: Nosferatu, a 1922 silent horror film, was an unauthorized adaptation of Bram Stoker's Dracula. Despite a court order to destroy it, copies survived and influenced cinema.

Title: Frankenstein: Legacy
Description: England, 1875. A century after Victor Frankenstein's doomed experiment, his journals have traded hands for decades.

Title: Cita
Description: A sexually charged story about a young woman who secretly sleeps with her husband's son. The two form an alliance to kill her husband but fate has other plans for Cita.

Title: Funny Birds
Description: Thrown together under tragic circumstances, three generations of women from the same family are forced to learn to live together on a small rural chicken farm in New Jersey, which generates moving and amusing situations.

Title: Pilot
Description: A story about a pilot who suddenly loses his job, then unexpectedly gets rehired with a new identity.

Title: Headwind
Description: When Alain Brel is supposed to play, his fate mixes with that of the artist. This encounter brings him closer to his daughter and turns his life upside down

Title: Thaghut
Description: Ainun found out that her biological father, Abah Mulya, was actually a spiritual teacher who taught heresy and distanced himself from the Qibla. Can Ainun guide them to the right path again?

Title: The Roast of Tom Brady
Description: Tom Brady faces the heat in this livestreamed, star-studded roast hosted by Kevin Hart.

Title: Daniela Forever
Description: Follows a man as he joins a sleep trial that allows him to rebuild his life with his girlfriend who died in an accident through the use of lucid dreams.

Title: The Mick and the Trick
Description: An Irish hit man working for a Cuban crime boss and the IRA tries to leave his life of crime with the help of a savvy hooker.

Title: The Perfect Mother
Description: A resilient mother escapes prison to reclaim her son and confront those who betrayed her

Title: Afternoons of Solitude
Description: Explores the spiritual pain of bullfighting, the tormented torero in a ring, one of the most excessive and graphic examples of the origin of Southern European civilization

Title: Out of Control
Description: A marriage is threatened when the husband's first love comes back to town.

Title: The Beach Boys
Description: A celebration of the legendary band that revolutionized pop music and created the harmonious sound that personified the California Dream.

Title: The Throwback
Description: A married couple are thrown into a crisis when the wife, an under-appreciated and stressed "supermom," suffers a post-traumatic breakdown during the holiday season, causing her to regress to her college-age, party-girl self.

Title: Mai
Description: Restlessly haunted by the past, Mai is greeted by a new dawn when she reluctantly befriends the neighborhood ladies' man. But when her yesterday catches up to her today, what will become of her tomorrow?

Title: Baby Invasion
Description: An ultra-realistic, multiplayer FPS game follows a group of mercenaries using baby faces as avatars. Tasked with entering mansions of the rich and powerful, players must explore every rabbit hole before time runs out.

Title: The Firefighters
Description: After drastic tragedies and changes, firefighters must see themselves helping out the entire world each day, even though in personal life and in work, going against all odds.

Title: Desert Road
Description: A woman crashes her car and walks down the road for help - only to find no matter which way she walks she ends up back at her crashed car again.

Title: Seven Cemeteries
Description: A recent parolee (Danny Trejo) gets a Mexican witch to resurrect his old posse so that they can help him save a woman's ranch from a ruthless drug lord.

Title: Zebra
Description: A group of white collar fraudsters become entangled with a vicious criminal as they plan an audacious heist.

Title: Waitress
Description: Three servers are willing to do everything to find their perfect mate. They are always ready to serve.

Title: Sew Torn
Description: A seamstress gets tangled in her own thread after stealing a briefcase from a drug deal gone bad. In an escalating game of cat and mouse, her different choices lead to drastically different outcomes along the way.

Title: Blue Rodeo: Lost Together
Description: A feature documentary about one of Canada's most beloved bands whose songs are like lifelong friends, having seeped into every stage of our lives. Theirs is a tale of determination, success and 40 of enduring friendships.

Title: Ebony Hustle 2: Ballistic Protection
Description: A female private investigator looks to correct a mistake from the past, before looking toward the future.

Title: Sisid Marino
Description: A married couple falls into depression after the death of their child. They turn to sex as a coping mechanism, but poverty takes its toll on them.

Title: Swede Caroline
Description: In this British Mockumentary, the competitive giant vegetable growing world is rocked by scandal when up-and-coming prospect Caroline has her prized marrow plants stolen.

Title: Who's Watching Us
Description: When Ruth is hired to babysit for the Harris family, her and the kids find out that someone else is watching them closely. Ruth and Jasmine has to fight to protect themselves and her little brother Micah.

Title: Ext. Masina. Noapte
Description: A bloody thriller (sort of Agatha Christie does The Twilight Zone) morphs into its own "making of", a really talky one - a conversation about film, about fear, about fiction. The type of film where the less you know, the better.

Title: Pater Noster and the Mission of Light
Description: Max, a young record store clerk stumbles upon a rare vinyl LP and is drawn into the world of a 1970s hippie commune. An invitation to the remnants of the cult and its unholy spawn leads to grave circumstances for Max and her friends.

Title: Hemet, or the Landlady Don't Drink Tea
Description: A tyrannical landlady lords it over her tenants during an epidemic, pitting them against each other in a web of paranoia spun for deadly results.

Title: Nokturno
Description: It centers on a Filipino family and a daughter who lives overseas as they get haunted by a primal and supernatural curse.

Title: Max Dagan
Description: Trying to get his dying father out of prison with a compassionate release, Max Dagan needs the help of the daughter of the man his father killed.

Title: Azzamine
Description: Azzam and Jasmine's love journey which started with an arranged marriage. Azzam is a pious, kind, gentle and patient man.

Title: Matka
Description: Rising through the ranks of the criminal world, a man becomes a key player in a massive nationwide gambling operation.

Title: Drive Back Home
Description: In 1970, a gruff New Brunswick plumber travels to Toronto to bail out his estranged gay brother jailed for public indecency. Reluctantly driving home together per their mother's wish, their tense reunion tests their sibling bond.

Title: Meet the Leroys
Description: A man takes his wife and their teenage children on a road trip down memory lane while facing divorce.

Title: The Twisters
Description: Dozens of deadly tornadoes converge in the Midwest, merging into a mega twister set to obliterate everything for hundreds of miles.

Title: Almost Paradise
Description: Ugo Conti, charismatic Italian aristocrat and influencer, arrives in Mexico where he seduces the Mexican high society. When he meets Frida Becker again, the love of his past, he will end up in the center of a struggle for political power.

Title: Cora
Description: After a deadly mist has wiped out most of humanity, a mysterious organisation is trying to save what's left of humankind.

Title: U Are the Universe
Description: After Earth explodes, Ukrainian space trucker Andriy Melnyk becomes the last person in the universe until he receives a call from Catherine, a French woman on a distant space station. Despite the obstacles, Andriy decides to find her.

Title: Extremely Unique Dynamic
Description: During their final weekend together, two best friends test the limits of their friendship while making a triple-meta film.

Title: Vaaradhi
Description: Chandra, a devoted husband, is left in a coma after a brutal attack. Upon waking, he discovers an imposter, Vinay, has taken his place and is dangerously obsessed with his wife, Nakshatra.

Title: The Last of the Sea Women
Description: On the shores of Jeju Island, a fierce group of South Korean divers fights to save their vanishing culture from looming threats.

Title: You Are the Apple of My Eye
Description: A group of close friends who attend a private school all have a debilitating crush on the sunny star pupil, Sun-ah. The only member of the group who claims not to is Jin-woo, but he ends up loving her as well.

Title: C4 Cinta
Description: Hari, Soniya, and friends traverse Singapore and Malaysia, confronting revived relationships, unvoiced realities. Their journeys explore love, memory, identity through emotional drama involving family and friendships.

Title: Mother's Instinct
Description: Love. Law. Loss. One choice will change everything.

Title: Mukadderat
Description: After the loss of her husband Sultan wants to remarry. Thus she finds herself in a new way.

Title: Stripped: Nashville
Description: This observational documentary follows the lives of Nashville's most dynamic exotic dancers over the course of several days - highlighting their skills as dancers, upbringing, personal relationships and business acumen.

Title: Karinyo Brutal
Description: When a battered mistress meets her neighbor, she knows he will be her perfect escape plan. But things turn chaotic when their plan backfires.

Title: Disco's Revenge
Description: Disco. Never. Died. DISCO'S REVENGE is a pulsating deep dive into the very soul of disco music and its impact across genres and history. Told by the people who created it, nurtured it, and in turn, discovered themselves on the dancefloor.

Title: Palipat-lipat, papalit-palit
Description: A guest turns into nightmare. Story revolves around protagonist and his wife. An Unwanted guest and her desire ruins their personal life. See who wins between lust and love.

Title: 0000 Kilometre
Description: A phone call to Izmir while she and Ege are living together in France turns their lives upside down. The caller claims to be Izmir's recently deceased mother.

Title: Transmitzvah
Description: A famous Yiddish singer returns to her childhood neighborhood in Buenos Aires to confront her family and her past.

Title: Bad Fish
Description: When a marine biologist investigates mysterious deadly attacks on fishermen in an Oregon coastal town, he discovers the culprit is a mermaid who must find a mate to breed with before returning to the sea.

Title: Le quatrième mur
Description: Georges, a politically committed stage director, has given up activism. But when Samuel, his best friend suffering from an incurable disease, urges him to pursue his crazy idea of staging Anouilh's Antigone to steal two hours of peace from the Lebanese war, Georges cannot refuse. In Beirut, George will rapidly discover the tense atmosphere and all the war conflicts between ethnic groups in the country. The play seems to be a glimmer of hope, even if the cloud of a raging war is upon them. How will the man who has only ever known revolt face the reality of the conflict? Will he be able to escape unscathed?

Title: The Lost Tiger
Description: Adopted by a wrestler kangaroo family, Teo's life changes when visions lead him to his roots. He embarks on an epic journey to save his homeland from destruction.

Title: Silent Bite
Description: A gang of bank robbers take shelter in a motel after a Christmas Eve bank heist, unbeknownst to them they are not the most dangerous thing seeking refuge on this cold Christmas night.

Title: Once Upon a Christmas Wish
Description: Mayor Brian Ortega is beloved in the idyllic community of Long Grove. While decorating for Christmas with the residents, Brian discovers his childhood Christmas wish list which magically begins to come true.

Title: Salawahan
Description: Melaine can't get enough with the two men in her life. When a new man arrives, she gives in to temptation.

Title: Roadkill
Description: Vengeance rides the open road when a young woman traveling alone encounters a renegade drifter and ends up in a fight for her life.

Title: Bermondsey Tales: Fall of the Roman Empire
Description: A gritty comedy-drama based on real events. Bermondsey Tales: Fall Of The Roman Empire tells the story of South London crime family The Roman's as infighting, cozzers and rival firms put everything they have worked for at risk.

Title: My Wifes X
Description: A newly released ex-con seeks revenge on his ex-wife and her new husband. As he pursues his vengeful mission, he remains unaware of a shocking connection between his target and someone closely involved in his release from prison.

Title: 2nd Miracle in Cell No. 7
Description: Two years have passed, and Kartika lives with Hendro and Linda. However, when Hendro agrees to adopt Kartika, the Social Service prevents it. The inmates in cell No. 7 and Hendro decide to fight for justice in their own way.

Title: Jesus Crown of Thorns
Description: Retelling Jesus' life in a way that shines a new light.

Title: Four Mothers
Description: A struggling novelist who is forced to take care of three eccentric older women - and his own mother - over the course of one chaotic weekend in Dublin.

Title: The Proud Princess
Description: Proud princess Krasomila lives isolated, her advisers scheme to marry her to a weakling; King Miroslav disguises as a gardener to cure her pride; they flee advisers' rage; she discovers his identity; they marry, advisers expelled.

Title: What We Wrote Together
Description: Mariano and Juan, a long-term couple, move from the city to start a plant nursery after Juan's writing career takes off. Their new rural life is interrupted by a visit from Juan's best friend bearing pivotal news.

Title: Something to Stand for with Mike Rowe
Description: Join America's favorite storyteller on an epic journey to the heart of Washington DC. This cinematic tour de force will take viewers to the frontlines of the American Revolution, World War II, the Civil Rights movement, and more.

Title: Trisha on the Rocks
Description: One fine night Trisha meets Vishal at a party. This meeting starts a super fun havoc with the cutest romance in their lives.

Title: Money Electric: The Bitcoin Mystery
Description: Cullen Hoback investigates the origins of Bitcoin and its anonymous creator Satoshi Nakamoto, exploring the potential of this cryptocurrency on the global financial system and who could hold immense power if it became mainstream.

Title: Ryan's World the Movie: Titan Universe Adventure
Description: Ryan's twin sisters Emma and Kate get trapped in a comic book world. Ryan enters this realm to rescue them, facing adventures, battles, and mishaps while attempting to bring them back before his parents discover their disappearance.

Title: Jack in Time for Christmas
Description: Jack Whitehall races against time to get from the US to the UK for Christmas. His frantic four-day journey involves various modes of transport and encounters with celebrity friends as he battles holiday chaos to reach home.

Title: The Lost Holliday
Description: When Cassandra Marshall learns that her estranged son Damien Holliday has died, she heads to L.A. to handle his arrangements. She arrives to find that they're being handled by her sons husband, Jason Holliday, who she knows nothing about.

Title: Reawakening
Description: A couple whose daughter aged 14 went missing and then reappears after a decade.

Title: The Park Maniac
Description: Based on a true story, an infamous serial killer, who assaulted and killed several women in the 90s, gets on a collision course with a young journalist eager for the truth and a career-changing article.

Title: Shukrana
Description: A close-knit family living in a rural community navigate marriage proposals and pregnancies, alongside a tragedy which threatens to tear them apart in this Punjabi language comedy drama.

Title: Maybe Baby 2
Description: Two couples discover their kids aren't swapped at the fertility clinic. They decide to cohabitate and jointly raise their respective biological children despite the initial mix-up.

Title: The Birds Who Fear Death
Description: Two brothers, disinherited and desperate for cash, journey into the Canadian wilds to find themselves, their people and their fortune.

Title: Last Stop: Rocafort St.
Description: A mystery that has shaken the Rocafort Metro station in Barcelona for years enters fully into Laura's life when she starts working at this old, quiet stop and discovers that many people have died there under strange circumstances.

Title: Over the Red River
Description: Follows a tenacious young widow who braves the perilous desert to free her kidnapped sister and wreak vengeance on the outlaws who murdered her husband, while also crossing paths with an ex-member of the same gang that ruined her life.

Title: Bozji gnjev
Description: Ilija is a member of the Croatian Defence Council (HVO) somewhere in Central Bosnia in late 1993. One morning, after a routine mine laying campaign, he learns his younger brother Goran was killed far beyond enemy lines, together with eight other soldiers. Through a friend from the secret service, he finds out the mission was an unofficial one and that Goran and the others were acting as mercenaries. Ilija begins to expose a network of illegal activity involving not only the military, but high-ranking officials. As the investigation becomes more dangerous, his original intention to find out the truth slowly turns into a pathological mission of vengeance.

Title: The Happiness I Have
Description: Dr. Ahmed, who is interested in giving advice to his followers about building character and marital happiness on social media while he faces problems in his marital life, is surprised when his wife proposes to her friend to marry him.

Title: Who Am I
Description: In one apartment, nine human conditions experience a contained life as they make the world their own.

Title: A Savior Red
