Description: Pat, a failed restaurateur, and Lara, a diner waitress, both divorced, cross paths. Pat employs his charm, cooking skills, and karaoke to court Lara, aiming to find romance in their shared dissatisfaction.

Title: A Hip Hop Story
Description: A pioneer of the culture joins forces with a few of rap music's elite performers to attempt to save hip hop.

Title: Mr. Bachchan
Description: A straight-laced income tax officer suspended due to his unwavering honesty returns to his hometown and falls in love with a woman who reciprocates his feelings, before he is reinstated and tasked with raiding the home of a powerful man.

Title: The Champion
Description: A hot-headed football star has it all until a fight gets him benched and assigned a new tutor: a reclusive academic who'll teach him to face his fears.

Title: In Flight
Description: The night before Claire Reynolds' trip to Paris, she catches the eye of a mysterious, handsome stranger. That's the last thing she remembers before waking up on a plane with no recollection of what happened after that.

Title: Ronny Chieng: Love to Hate It
Description: Comedian Ronny Chieng shares humorous insights on topics like IVF, online discourse, politics, and generational divides during a sold-out, multi-night show.

Title: Isolation
Description: Jovan, a young biologist, gets a well-paying job in a forest, but when he checks the cameras he discovers a man and as time goes by the night calls, strange sounds and isolation plunge him into paranoia.

Title: Viet and Nam
Description: In the underground coal mines, Nam and Viet, young miners, face danger and darkness. One prepares to leave for a new life, but they must find Nam's father's remains, a soldier lost in a faraway forest, retracing the past through memories.

Title: Do Aur Do Pyaar
Description: A couple on the brink of a breakup are cheating on each other with two sexy outsiders. Whilst they're waiting to reveal their secret and go their separate ways, life has other plans for them.

Title: Nonkonform
Description: Dietrich Kuhlbrodt: Hitler boy, film critic, actor, senior prosecutor, screenwriter, punk musician, temporary porn commissioner, and family man.

Title: Sallywood
Description: When Zack, a 20-something writer, moves from Maine to Hollywood to pursue his career dreams, he meets his favorite actress, Sally Kirkland, who hires him on the spot to be her personal assistant, and so much more.

Title: The Silent Planet
Description: Follows two inmates in the near future who are sentenced to a lifetime of hard labor on a distant planet. As things unravel, they become increasingly paranoid and start to lose a sense of who they are and their past lives.

Title: Go Away
Description: During a family gathering, dinner is interrupted by a knock at the door. 5 intruders take the guests hostage and put them through a series of sadistic games. As the night goes on, the intruders realize they also may have something to fear.

Title: I Hate Myself and Want to Die
Description: A depressed young guy is trying to kill himself but he keeps getting interrupted by his unsuspecting family and friends.

Title: Till Death Do Us Part
Description: A woman named Renata who is the wife of a man named Edwin. But unfortunately, their marriage did not run healthily, it was really toxic.

Title: Concerto for Abigail
Description: A pianist confronts progressive hearing loss as she falls for someone new. She must decide whether to shut herself off or let her love in and face the challenge together

Title: Rasavathi
Description: A former criminal doctor and his wife seek a tranquil life, but an inspector hellbent on vengeance jeopardizes their newfound peace.

Title: Mistura
Description: A woman's life unravels after her husband's betrayal isolates her from elite society. Embracing disregarded communities, she embarks on a transformative journey, challenging norms through a daring culinary venture that redefines her life.

Title: Visiting Hours
Description: The wives of two inmates serving time in the same penitentiary develop a surprising kinship.

Title: Who by Fire
Description: Seventeen-year-old Jeff stays at film director Blake Cadieux's wilderness lodge after being invited by friend Max's family. When strange events occur, Jeff suspects something is amiss with the director and his retreat.

Title: Killer Babes
Description: Three girlfriends, neglected and mistreated by their husbands, plan to take revenge on them with the help of an experienced man in this type of job.

Title: Last Night at Terrace Lanes
Description: When a bloodthirsty cult invades a bowling alley on its final night of operation, a high schooler on a date from hell, must join forces with her survivalist dad to fend off the crazed murderers.

Title: Gaucho Gaucho
Description: A celebration of Argentine Gauchos, a community of cowboys and cowgirls living beyond the modern world's boundaries.

Title: Hakkenden
Description: Bakin Takizawa, a popular Edo period author, begins to recount a story he is planning in front of his friend, the artist Hokusai Katsushika. The story is about eight warriors who, each carrying a jewel, gather together as if guided by fate and embark on a harsh journey to fight the curse of the Satomi family. Hokusai is drawn to Bakin's story and visits Bakin on various occasions to hear the rest of the story, and a strange relationship between the two begins. However, as the story finally approaches its climax, Bakin begins to lose his sight. With the completion of the story in question, he receives an unexpected proposal from his daughter-in-law. Will the story ever be completed?

Title: Forbidden Desire
Description: Agatha and Ubel's turbulent romance leads to a devastating breakup. Though she finds a new partner, Agatha can't get enough of Ubel. They continue their illicit affair until she finds out that Ubel has a secret that can ruin her life.

Title: 3391 Kilometres
Description: A lonely Turkish girl meets a boy who lives in a small town of France. Despite living far apart, they bond over shared quirks. Through late night chats they become close, overcoming physical distance to find friendship.

Title: The Great Ambition
Description: Biopic telling the life of the great and popular political leader Enrico Berlinguer, who almost led Italy's Communist Party into power in 1978.

Title: Six jours
Description: A police officer who was unable to find the killer of a young girl 11 years earlier. When another child is kidnapped in the same way just days before the case is closed for good, he decides to reinvestigate the unresolved kidnapping.

Title: Scared to Death
Description: A group of filmmakers attend a seance at an abandoned children's orphanage in order to do research for a movie...that's their first mistake.

Title: They Whisper
Description: A young boy emerges from a coma after a fall down an abandoned mine shaft. His family is confronted by dark, threatening spirits and the possibility that the child in their home might no longer be their son.

Title: Addition
Description: A heartwarming rom-com celebrating self-acceptance and the things in life that really count.

Title: Pay Dirt: The Story of Supercross
Description: The essence of Supercross, showcasing top riders and their quest for championships. It blends stunning visuals, rare footage, and interviews to reveal the passion and commitment behind this demanding sport.

Title: Maharot
Description: Tantan is a small-town young man, falls for Joni, a free-spirited woman who sells herself yet teaches him about love. As their bond deepens, will their love defy life's twists?

Title: Octopus with Broken Arms
Description: The wealthy businessman Zheng Bingrui invited his daughter Tingting's teacher Li Huiping and classmates' parents to a party at home. Unexpectedly, Tingting was kidnapped. Police officer Zhang Jingxian led the team to investigate.

Title: Brief History of a Family
Description: A middle-class family's fate becomes intertwined with their only son's enigmatic new friend in post one-child policy China, putting unspoken secrets, unmet expectations, and untended emotions under the microscope.

Title: Andrea Gets a Divorce
Description: A policewoman wants a divorce and city job promotion but after hitting her drunk husband with her car in an accidental collision, she flees the scene, committing a hit-and-run.

Title: Half-Life of Memory: America's Forgotten Atomic Bomb Factory
Description: In the suburbs of Denver, the U.S. secretly manufactured thousands of atomic weapons, leaving behind a toxic legacy that will persist for generations.

Title: From Darkness
Description: Park ranger Angelica and ex-Viktor investigate a missing woman's case in a Swedish nature reserve. They explore haunted caves, face their past, and uncover dark secrets while battling a mythical creature.

Title: Enchanting Christmas
Description: A father's ice sculpture of a princess magically comes to life, causing unexpected disruptions in the lives of those she meets.

Title: Deadly Fiancée
Description: When Jenny's father marries a younger woman, her mother goes into "mama-bear" mode when she becomes suspicious of the young woman's intentions.

Title: Don't F**k with Ghosts
Description: Filmmaking duo, Adam and Stu are convinced they need to capitalize on the next paranormal phenomenon, attempting to prove that ghosts are real.

Title: The Carters
Description: It's vaccinated vs unvaccinated after a vaccine proves deadly. For Flame and his crew, it's now survival of the fittest after they enter a home seeking shelter from the dangers that lurk in the night.

Title: Abraham Ozler
Description: Revolves around the personal and professional lives of veteran cop Abraham Ozler, ACP Trichur, who at one time has to take up a serial killing case and the mysterious hunt begins.

Title: Come Closer
Description: When Eden's brother tragically dies, her grief spirals into obsession after discovering his secret girlfriend. A haunting exploration of love, loss and fixation with stunning visuals.

Title: Prodigieuses
Description: Twin sisters, driven by passion for piano, join an elite music university. Diagnosed with a debilitating illness threatening their hands, they refuse to abandon their dream, fighting to reinvent themselves as prodigious pianists.

Title: Article 20
Description: A prosecutor on his last case deals with a colleague to exonerate a suspect, making the law just.

Title: Ghost Cat Anzu
Description: Friendship shared between Karin, a strong-minded girl sent to live with her monk granddad in the Japanese countryside, and Anzu, the even-more unpredictable phantom feline who acts as her guardian.

Title: The Lady of the Lake
Description: A grief-stricken Native American woman investigates the legend of the Lady of the Lake, determined to unravel its mysteries after her brother's tragic demise.

Title: Camp Blood: Clown Shark
Description: After being dispatched by a young woman with the special ability to see horrendous murders in her visions, the evil spirit of the Camp Blood Killer passes into that fiercest of aquatic predators, The Great White Shark. And when the killings begin anew, leaving law enforcement baffled, this courageous heroine must return to the woods of the infamous Camp Blood to face off again with a newly reincarnated killer before it's too late for everyone.

Title: Doc of Chucky
Description: The ultimate account of the Child's Play film franchise. With contributions from cast, crew, and more, experience the story that proves you can't keep a good guy down in a series of films that have created an icon.

Title: Janaka Aithe Ganaka
Description: A young married man rejects parenthood, calculating costs for a child's upbringing. He determines his income insufficient for education, quality of life, and other expenses, leading to his decision against having children at that time.

Title: Just a Couple of Days
Description: After being reassigned from music to field reporting, a critic goes to a refugee camp near Paris during an evacuation. He experiences police violence and is thrust into becoming the face of the refugee cause.

Title: Seeking Mavis Beacon
Description: Investigates the disappearance and reexamines the legacy of one of the most influential Black women in technology.

Title: Operation Valentine
Description: Showcasing the indomitable spirits of the Indian Air Force heroes on the frontlines and the challenges they face during one of the biggest, fiercest aerial attacks that India has ever seen.

Title: First Taste
Description: Yuna, a woman engaged with her long time boyfriend, Nicco, starts to have second thoughts when she meets again her first love, Becca. Now she is torn between the man she loves and the woman she first loved.

Title: Steppenwolf
Description: Tamara searches for her missing son in a violent town. She hires a morally questionable ex-detective to find him. His methods are cruel but she is determined to find her son whatever the cost.

Title: Crisis Negotiators
Description: Senior Negotiator Cheuk Man Wai accidentally becomes the number one suspect in a murder case. He is forced to occupy the police station and take the police hostage. He also appoints former negotiator Tse Ka Chun to talk to him.

Title: Ravens
Description: The dark fantasy love story of legendary Japanese photographer Masahisa Fukase and his wife Yoko.

Title: A Few Moments of Cheers
Description: Kanata, a high school student who loves making music videos, finds purpose and inspiration after watching a street performance by Yu, a teacher who abandoned her dreams of having a music career.

Title: Amityville: Where the Echo Lives
Description: When paranormal investigator Heather West receives a call from a terrified woman who claims her house is inhabited by a ghost, she discovers the building has a horrifying history.

Title: I Am the Secret in Your Heart
Description: Swooning over a charming transfer student, a high school teen becomes entangled in a love triangle between her crush and a close childhood friend.

Title: Two Blue Hearts
Description: Reunited after years apart, a young couple faces a new chapter of parenthood as they negative challenges in raising their 4-year-old son together.

Title: The Train of Death
Description: Bloody terror wiped out the Sangkara Train carriages one by one, putting passengers at risk of life and death.

Title: Chuck Zito: An American Story
Description: Follows multi-talented and versatile Chuck Zito: Boxer, martial arts expert, bodyguard, stunt man, actor, and ex-president of the New York Hells Angels club.

Title: Nefarious
Description: A fast moving, funny and ultimately tragic European road movie about two hedonistic outlaws and their quest to open up a coffeeshop in Amsterdam.

Title: Himas
Description: Dana is wife to a blind ex-fireman who is unable to satisfy his wife's physical needs due to his condition. A young man enters the picture and lures Dana to a sinful relationship to satisfy her sexual frustrations.

Title: Erdal ile Ece 2
Description: Lifestyle changes, cheating scares and a series of hilarious misadventures put an otherwise happily married couple's love to the test.

Title: The Mountain Within Me
Description: When faced with life changing injuries, Ed Jackson harnessed the power of positivity and determination to deliver a future for himself, that most thought impossible.

Title: Devaki Nandana Vasudeva
Description: Driven by fears of astrological prophecy, Kamsaraja torments his sister's family, convinced her child will cause his downfall. When imprisoned, Krishna shields the family from Kamsaraja's sinister schemes.

Title: Bang Bang
Description: Tim Blake Nelson stars as 'Bang Bang' Rozyski, an eccentric retired pugilist obsessed with rectifying the sins of his past.

Title: Havnaa
Description: Follows real-life happenings of Magne Havnaa, Norway's first cruiserweight boxing champion in 1990 by defeating American Richard Pultz. His brother Erling was a top-ranked kickboxer who later participated in Norway's largest robbery.

Title: Victory
Description: A high school dance duo and a soccer team on a remote island. Two girls create a cheer leading club to pursue their love of dance, but they soon find themselves enthusiastically cheering on the soccer team and the entire island.

Title: In the Name of Blood
Description: In the working-class neighborhoods of Nice, a pillar of the local Georgian community is murdered. His son Tristan, who aspires to become an orthodox priest, finds himself alone with his grieving mother. Gabriel, his older brother with a troubled past, reappears and returns from a long exile to make amends by washing away his family's honor.

Title: Love, Danielle
Description: Amid family drama and dysfunction, a woman who carries a BRCA gene mutation must decide whether or not to remove her breasts and ovaries to reduce her cancer risk.

Title: Naam
Description: A professional killer loses his memory after a near-fatal mishap. Piecing his life, he's ensnared in a perilous game with the CBI and implacable foes. Every revelation about his past uncovers deeper enigmas, that changes everything.

Title: Space Sharks
Description: A military experiment conducted on a space station goes horribly wrong, sending a new breed of weaponized sharks to earth with only one mission: destroy everything in their path.

Title: Oshi no Ko: The Final Act
Description: Goro is a gynecologist and idol fan who's in shock after his favorite star, Ai, announces an impromptu hiatus. Little does Goro realize that he's about to forge a bond with her that defies all common sense!. Lies are an idol's weapon!.

Title: Eye for an Eye 2
Description: A blind swordsman reluctantly mentors an orphan seeking vengeance for his destroyed family, teaching him martial arts skills. The orphan waits for an opportunity to avenge his kin.

Title: Ajab Raat Ni Gajab Vaat
Description: YouTuber Kartik is persuaded by friend Nilay to elope with girlfriend, but reaches the wrong address. A different girl accompanies them, leading to complications.

Title: Clickbait: Unfollowed
Description: A group of influencers are invited to a house for a competition with deadly consequences.

Title: Ten Toes Down
Description: Detective Andrea Oya and FBI agent Samantha Curry team up to solve a string of murders targeting Black women and children, leaving cryptic marks on the victims. As they face danger, they forge a powerful bond.

Title: Cheech and Chong's Last Movie
Description: Exploring their 5-decade career performing stand-up, making records, and starring in hit films. It covers their lives, comedy partnership, and lasting influence on pop culture.

Title: Plea
Description: After 20 years in prison, a man wrongfully convicted of rape and murder is released. He reconnects with his now adult daughter and tries to rebuild his life. The victim's husband has become a recluse, obsessed with a true crime documentary about the case, and tries to contact law enforcement to reopen the investigation, but they consider it closed. Then the prosecutor is kidnapped in a desperate attempt to convince her to find the real killer.

Title: Three Days of Fish
Description: This black-and-white drama/comedy explores the strained relationship between Gerrie and his son Dick during their annual three-day reunion in Rotterdam, with the looming threat that this might be Gerrie's last visit.

Title: 6 Hours Away
Description: It follows ex-Marine Chris Montano after his wife goes missing during a business trip. He then finds himself in a race against time to save her.

Title: Justicia artificial
Description: In the near future, the Government aims to replace judges with Artificial Intelligence software, pledging to effectively automate and depoliticise the justice system. Carmen Costa, a distinguished judge, has been invited to assess this new procedure. However, when the software's creator is found dead, she realizes her life is in danger and that she will have to fight the powerful interests that are at play in the highest echelons of the State. Galician Simón Casal takes the debate the boundaries of Artificial Intelligence one step further in a gripping thriller of political conspiracies.

Title: The Parades
Description: A mother searches for her missing son after a devastating calamity, only to realize that she has died and is now confined to a realm of restless spirits.

Title: Bhai Ni Beni Ladki
Description: A tale depicting the relationship between a brother and his sister.

Title: Remember Us
Description: An unlikely friendship forms between a young offender undertaking community service and a dementia sufferer. Lucas has been hanging around with the wrong crowd but delivering food boxes to the elderly gives him a new sense of purpose.

Title: Beyond the Likes
Description: Follows five friends in 2008 Chicago becoming social media influencers. One friend, Cam, falls for wealthy heiress Nefertari from Abu Dhabi, igniting cultural clashes threatening their relationship as they navigate adulthood's challenges.

Title: Konchitsya leto
Description: After a long absence, the young guy Kesha returns to the village. His father and younger brother are waiting for him. Kesha - twenty-seven. He has time behind him. He returned and wants to just live - find some work, save up money, and then decide what to do next. His brother Tima is only seventeen. He has a school behind him, he dreams of going to college - on a "budget". And everything seems to be going according to plan. Tima gets high scores at the introductory, Kesha gets a job in a gold mining artel. But very quickly, Kesha is "thrown" by prospectors, and he is left without a job and a future and decides to take revenge. He steals the gold and goes on the run. But not alone, but together with his younger brother.

Title: Riviera
Description: A dying palm tree, a doomed romance, and a mother who wants to move on. This will be Alkistis' last summer on the Athenian Riviera.

Title: Sons of Rizk 3
Description: Four brothers engage in criminal acts but vow to go straight someday. After a deal unravels, the eldest sibling wants to quit crime, yet his defiant younger brothers make a risky deal with a notorious criminal overlord.

Title: The Omicron Killer
Description: Attacked by vicious thugs, left severely wounded and hospitalized, a serial killer known as The Omicron Killer vows vengeance as he embarks on a new reign of terror.

Title: The Murder of Sandra Rivett
Description: While the hunt for Lucan has dominated the media for half a century, the name of the victim, Sandra Rivett has been forgotten.

Title: Family Padam
Description: Being a middle class family that can afford movie tickets, they dream of producing a whole new movie to fulfill their younger son's wish to rediscover himself which brings grave challenges.

Title: Touched by Eternity
Description: Fatso lives in a run-down trailer, spending his days listening to podcasts about immortality. One day, his monotonous life is disrupted by two unexpected visitors-vampires Egons and Carlos-who offer him the eternal life he's longed for.

Title: In Our Blood
Description: Filmmaker Emily Wyland reunites with estranged mother for documentary. When mother disappears, Emily and cinematographer Danny pursue clues to her whereabouts amidst traces of her past addictions.

Title: Thirsty for Likes
Description: From the outside, Diamond and Harmony are living the high life as influencers. What no one knows is what they've had to endure behind closed doors.

Title: Crust
Description: A depressed has-been child actor and owner of a dingy laundromat, becomes powerfully vengeful when his collection of lone socks transforms into a protective, cute, murderous monster named Crust.

Title: Little Emma
Description: A miniature girl raised by animal parents journeys to an island of tiny humans, uncovering unsettling revelations about her origins.

Title: Unsinkable
Description: Award-winning film about the political intrigue and drama during the inquiry and investigation into the sinking of Titanic.

Title: Non Negotiable
Description: Alan Binder is a skillful hostage negotiator, the best in Mexico, who will soon face the most crucial case of his career when the President and his lover are kidnapped. The kidnapper demands to negotiate only with him.

Title: Now or Never!
Description: On March 15, 1848, a young firebrand poet, Sándor Petöfi ignites the Hungarian Revolution with his passionate 'National Song', prompting the Austrians to dispatch a ruthless secret agent to assassinate him and suppress the uprising.

Title: Albany Road
Description: On her way to the most important meeting of her career, a New York executive is forced to share a rental car with her ex-fiancé's mother, only to discover that the mother is hiding a major secret.

Title: Silvio
Description: During a kidnapping, television personality Silvio Santos must fight to protect his family and his legacy while facing one of the most challenging moments of his life.

Title: Nobody Dumps My Daughter
Description: After Jimmy breaks up with Theresa, her obsessive mother Mary tries desperately to reunite them, even hiring a hitman to kill Jimmy when bribing him fails.

Title: You Will Die in 6 Hours
Description: Jun Woo alerts Jeong Yun about her upcoming murder. Skeptical, she investigates, uncovering Jun Woo's link to serial killings. She races to learn if he's protecting or deceiving her before her prophesized death.

Title: Mommy Meanest
Description: A teenage girl is relentlessly cyber-bullied, but the worst part is when she finds out who is actually sending the horrific texts.

Title: Yo no soy esa
Description: Susana fell in a coma in 1999. On 2024 she wake up to be stuck in a grown woman's body but emotionally and psychologically still a teenager, trying to reconnect with a world where nothing is familiar for her.

Title: Happiness Is
Description: Turning forty was meant to be a low-key event for Princess, but when her best friend throws her an unforgettable party, her entire world is shaken up.

Title: Zbory OSBB
Description: Residents of a Ukrainian apartment building gather to discuss the purchase of a common generator for the winter, but its capacity is not enough for everyone.

Title: Drone
Description: Émilie, a young student, works as a cam-girl at night to make ends meet. One evening, a mysterious drone appears at her apartment window. From then on, whenever Emilie is alone, the drone appears and follows her.

Title: Shark Warning
Description: Two decades later, a man returns to his hometown after a shark killed his brother. When the shark resurfaces and claims more victims, he forms alliances to hunt down and eliminate the predator once and for all.

Title: The Freshly Cut Grass
Description: Pablo, a university professor, becomes romantically involved with a student. At the same time, Natalia, a university professor, becomes romantically involved with a student. Two paralleled stories, similar but different at the same time.

Title: The Gifts of Christmas
Description: When Taya, the hardworking owner of a struggling resort, reconnects with Bradley, they must navigate financial challenges, fraudulent activities, and their own complicated history to save the resort and find love in the process.

Title: Family Matters
Description: Cita conspires with her stepson to murder her husband, only to face a cruel twist of fate, while Mara, a struggling student caring for a dying patriarch, is caught in the chaos when his estranged son returns.

Title: Here's Yianni!
Description: Elderly diner owner Yianni slips into a fractured mind state, imagining hosting a talk show. His wife Plousia becomes his caregiver as his dementia worsens. Thinking a boy is their lost son, Yianni reunites their families.

Title: Sins of the Bride
Description: A bride's fling with the best man puts her in danger when her fiancé returns and the secret threatens to destroy their happily-ever-after.

Title: Must auk
Description: A comical triptych about residents in an apartment block district who long for a better life. When a black hole mysteriously appears in a lilac bush, they will have to face aliens, a giant spider, and an Austrian in breeches.

Title: Last Swim
Description: On A-level results day, an ambitious Iranian-British teen in London grapples with a major life decision while hanging out with friends across the city.

Title: Shark Girl
Description: When a beautiful young influencer survives a mysterious shark attack, she becomes a monstrous apex predator, hunting and feeding in sunny Venice Beach, California.

Title: Schneewittchen
Description: Snow White declines the Prince's offer to witness the Evil Queen and the Hunter's intimate encounter, quipping she'd prefer to hear about it instead.

Title: La Familia
Description: A father spends all the family's savings on a multi-level company - with unexpected consequences.

Title: Its Name Was Mormo
Description: A young family's life unravels into chaos as a sinister presence targets each member in its own malicious manner. Through the lens of police evidence, Mark, Diana, and Mia endure the torment of a demon deeply rooted in Greek mythology.

Title: Cash Storm
Description: Bank Robbers crash their getaway car in the path of a tornado and all the money gets sucked into a funnel cloud. Two scientists rescue the robbers along with a chatty influencer and embark on a comical odyssey.

Title: The Forbidden Camp: Mass Possession
Description: A group of students enjoying camping activities. Instead of being a fun moment, the atmosphere becomes tense when one by one they are possessed by evil forces.

Title: The Vord
Description: An ancient Nordic entity recruits a corrupt priest to deliver a woman's soul as a gift. Caught between her pagan roots and the church, she must resist those she once trusted as a spirit guide struggles to redeem them.

Title: Till Death Do Us Part
Description: A wedding planner must keep her best friend and her groom safe from a psychotic stranger who secretly threatens to murder the entire party.

Title: Sunny
Description: Sunny is the story of a middle-aged woman who dreams to fulfill her dying wish to reunite with high school friends.

Title: Sheriff
Description: Sheriff and Nazri, police officers from different departments, team up to take down Tony, a ruthless drug kingpin running a methamphetamine syndicate responsible for numerous deaths, known as the Meth Killer.

Title: Siren
Description: An ambulance driver turned criminal eagerly awaits his release from prison, but it takes 14 years.

Title: Love Story
Description: Tells the love story of a model and a director.

Title: The School Duel
Description: When an opportunity for twisted notoriety arises, a tormented 13-year old, Sammy, enlists in a deadly competition.

Title: 40 Acres
Description: In a post-apocalyptic world with food scarcity, a Black family of Canadian farmers descended from American Civil War migrants defend their homestead against cannibals trying to seize their resources.

Title: In Good Hands 2
Description: A newly reunited father and son grapple with new beginnings after tragedy, but can they manage to fill the void left by a beloved wife and mother?

Title: Spermworld
Description: Three men enter the new wild west of baby making - online forums where sperm donors connect with hopeful parents - but find themselves exchanging more than just genetic material.

Title: Aranmanai 4
Description: After his sister's suspicious death, a man decides to discover the hidden truth, setting off a chasm for chaos and terror.

Title: Locha Laapsi
Description: An engineer's road trip to Kutch-Bhuj takes an unexpected turn when he unwittingly joins a ride with a man transporting a dead body and harboring a sinister secret, leading to a thrilling and comedic adventure.

Title: Yasam Koçu
Description: Failing to confess his love and reluctantly accompanying the famous actress Helin as a mandatory friend Cafer who mocked life coaches, energetic individuals, fortune-tellers, suddenly finds himself as the country's most popular life coach.

Title: Viktor
Description: Deeply personal audiovisual experience capturing a Deaf person's navigation through the Russian invasion of Ukraine and its ensuing chaos.

Title: Next to Us
Description: Former classmates were planned to participate in reality show, but on the road to location were attacked by a group of terrorists and left in the wilderness in a completely unknown and mysterious area.

Title: Citizen of a Kind
Description: After a fire destroys her laundromat, a single mother is tricked by a voice phishing scheme. She decides to investigate the criminals behind it.

Title: Paranoia
Description: Lulu ends up in the hospital, and sees a girl crying for help. When Lulu awakes, the girl is gone. But from here everything changes in Lulu's life. It's like someone or something is following her.

Title: Amp House Massacre
Description: A group of social media influencers sharing a mansion in the Hollywood Hills find themselves caught in a life and death game of survival as a killer reveals their deepest secrets before killing them off one by one.

Title: Greenwood Rising: The Rise of Black Wall Street
Description: The life of O.W. Gurley, a trailblazing Black entrepreneur, and his unwavering spirit that built Greenwood District into the thriving economic hub known as Black Wall Street, overcoming adversity in 1920s Tulsa, Oklahoma.

Title: Space Command Redemption
Description: Space Command hopeful vision of the future, a space-going saga featuring Walking Dead's Ethan McDowell, Star Trek Discovery's Doug Jones, Star Trek Voyager's Robert Picardo, and Babylon 5's Mira Furlan, Bruce Boxleitner and Bill Mumy.

Title: Vindicating Trump
Description: Dinesh D'Souza examines the challenges faced by Donald Trump, including political opposition, legal battles, and assassination attempts, during his bid to return to the presidency.

Title: Divorce
Description: Two decades after divorcing and taking separate paths in life, a former couple is working to obtain an official declaration of invalidity of their brief marriage.

Title: Mechanic Rocky
Description: A mechanic uncovers a sinister plot during a feud with local gangsters over ownership of his father's garage in this twisty Telugu-language action drama.

Title: Odio el verano
Description: Comedy about three couples who unknowingly book the same house for their family vacation, turning summer into a comical exercise in tolerance.

Title: Holy Rosita
Description: Rosita is a cheerful woman with an eager desire to have children. Those around her think it is irresponsible because she can barely take care of herself. When Rosita does become pregnant, she decides to keep it a secret.

Title: Paper Flowers
Description: Paper Flowers-a USC grad's quest for change in Peru is cut short by cancer. Back home, he finds strength in family and his college love. Shalin's viral manifesto urges cherishing every moment-a true tale of love, legacy, and now.

Title: Technoboys
Description: Twenty years after topping charts, Technoboys reunite to reclaim the pop throne but must battle newer groups in a changed music world. The lead singer has hidden motives to return.

Title: Hacking Hate
Description: A brave journalist adopts a fake identity to infiltrate online white supremacist groups, revealing dangerous networks of hate and extremism spreading across international borders.

Title: Onegin
Description: Evgeniy Onegin lives in grand style: balls, receptions, theater premieres and other entertainment that the capital can offer a young man. But social life has long tired him, so he perceives the news of the illness of his uncle living in the village as an opportunity to escape from the disgusting world. However, having reached the estate, Onegin learns about the death of a relative, which, however, does not upset Evgeniy too much. His financial affairs are very sad, and his uncle is rich and has no other heirs. Onegin locks himself in the estate, shuns his neighbors, who very soon begin to call him an eccentric among themselves. Evgeniy lives in aimless solitude until the owner, who has returned from abroad, appears at the neighboring estate - a young, enthusiastic Lenskiy, not yet satiated with life, who introduces Evgeniy to the sisters Tatyana and Olga Larin.

Title: Killer Influence
Description: In the midst of summer, Alex, an influencer, invites a few friends to her isolated country house. One evening, after streaming video, they are visited by a persistent stalker - The begining of a dreadful night they'll never forget.

Title: Fiore mio
Description: To paraphrase Suzanne Simard, this film is not about how we can save the mountain. It is about how the mountain could save us.

Title: The Private Eye
Description: The life of private eye, Mort Madison, is spiraling downward, when a beguiling, slightly familiar woman hires him for his most unusual case.

Title: The Opera!
Description: Modern version of Orpheus and Eurydice.

Title: La guitarra flamenca de Yerai Cortés
Description: La guitarra flamenca de Yerai Cortés is a story that combines the power of music with the weight of a family secret that must come to light. Starring Yerai Cortés himself, the plot explores themes of passion, love and forgiveness as the protagonist confronts the hidden truths of his family. Wrapped in a unique musical experience, this story not only highlights the power of flamenco as a means of expression, but also addresses Yerai's internal conflict.

Title: Alix
Description: A young girl is recruited to be a child soldier in the Colombian jungle and copes with her circumstances by using her imagination to journey to a magical realm.

Title: Viva La Vida
Description: A young woman who needs a kidney transplant wants to marry someone who will be able to donate a kidney, and meets a young man who has a brain disease.

Title: Boy Kaldag
Description: A man famous for being well-endowed, drives women wild and sparks envy among other men. As his legend grows, Boy Kaldag plunges into a world of lust and chaos that comes with his special characteristic.

Title: The Manifestation
Description: When a desperate day trader manifests a twin version of his wife to help him win trades, he soon discovers she may have a much darker agenda.

Title: Ghost Game
Description: Follows a thrill-seeking couple who set their target in an haunted house and endure various incidents as they witness a family going mad.

Title: Ancika
Description: In 1995, Dilan, the former motorcycle gang leader, fell in love with Ancika, a woman who hated motorcycle gangs. Furthermore, Ancika didn't like dating, so Dilan had to find a way to conquer her, a very different woman from Milea, his ex.

Title: Sattam En Kaiyil
Description: An accident leads Gowtham to conceal a body in his car. Arrested for drunk driving, his impounded vehicle at the police station holds the hidden corpse. Complications ensue, compelling him to find an escape from the perilous circumstances.

Title: Smoke Signals
Description: Brussels, 2012. After the Health Commissioner's abrupt dismissal shrouded in secrecy, MEP José Bové and his team launch an investigation into the matter.

Title: The Beldham
Description: A struggling new mother fights a generations-old presence lurking within her family home, threatening her safety, her sanity, and the life of her infant child.

Title: The Miranda Brothers
Description: An orphan rescued from trash becomes devoted to his elder brother, both growing to be star footballers - till the suspicious death of their mother threatens to tear them apart.

Title: Texas Cult House
Description: High school friends party at the abandoned home of a former cult leader and discover a mysterious anointing oil that holds the secret to the cult's unraveling. Austin, one of the teens, is haunted by childhood trauma.

Title: Happy Holidays
Description: In this panoramic family drama by Oscar-nominated Palestinian director Scandar Copti, personal quests, poor choices, and social pressures test cherished relationships, both well-worn and blooming.

Title: Skeletons in the Closet
Description: Haunted by a malevolent spirit since childhood, a desperate mother allows herself to become possessed in order to save the life of her terminally ill daughter.

Title: Elizabeth Taylor: The Lost Tapes
Description: Newly discovered interviews with Elizabeth Taylor and unprecedented access to the star's personal archive reveal the complex inner life and vulnerability of the groundbreaking icon.

Title: Alakada: Bad and Boujee
Description: A woman whose flashy and glamorous reputation is based entirely on lies hits trouble when her web of deceit starts falling apart.

Title: Beautiful Rebel
Description: The origin story of one of Italy's greatest rock stars, Gianna Nannini, who chased her dream despite obstacles from her family and the music industry.

Title: Death of the Sheik
Description: In 1926, silent film star Rudolph Valentino collapses during a movie tour. As he lies in hospital, fever dreams blur his glamorous Hollywood life with harsh reality, revealing the gap between his iconic status and personal struggles.

Title: Ishq Vishk Rebound
Description: Follows the lives of four young people who become enmeshed in a web of friendship, love, and self-discovery.

Title: Riders
Description: Nut, a young rider, got to know a beautiful girl named Pie by chance, but when Pie mysteriously disappeared, Nut and two other rider friends went out to find her.

Title: Maliko
Description: Eunice, a sexually fluent medical agent, befriended Mariko's local partner and seduced them both to satisfy their desires in a game of provocative sexual adventures.

Title: 2B Honest
Description: Murder, love, insurance policies. On the run from the law, Kato Roberts stumbles into a secret community that throws him into a world of chaos.

Title: This Too Shall Pass
Description: Simon, a 16-year-old suffocated by his strict Mormon upbringing, rebels and crosses the border with friends for a weekend in Canada, as they individually discover more about themselves.

Title: Firecracker
Description: When a heist goes dramatically wrong, leaving a hostage in peril, an unlikely trio find themselves fighting for their lives and their sanity on bonfire night.

Title: The Village Next to Paradise
Description: A newly formed family confronts challenges while pursuing individual goals and facing the intricacies of modern life, relying on love, trust, and resilience to guide them.

Title: Throuple's a Crowd
Description: Ysay and Hannah search for a new partner after losing their boyfriend, while a married couple's reunion with an old friend takes a turn when the guest becomes romantically involved with them both, unraveling two stories of love and desire.

Title: K3 en Het Lied van de Zeemeermin
Description: Hanne, Marthe and Julia have the vacation of a lifetime in the coastal village of Porto Sirento. Sun, sea, beach, having fun together, dancing and singing songs. But their vacation suddenly turns completely upside down, when a mysterious spell turns the girls into beautiful mermaids. If the girls do not want to stand out, they will have to avoid water, and of course that is easier said than done. Danger lurks everywhere. In the coastal village where the girls are enjoying their vacation, for some reason the inhabitants see mermaids as monsters. When the girls discover that after three days they will remain mermaids forever, a race against time begins to break the spell. If they don't succeed in time, Hanne, Marthe and Julia will be mermaids forever, and never again K3.

Title: Free Falling
Description: The perfect life of a strict and tough rhythmic gymnastics teacher of competition begins to escape out of her hands.

Title: Deadly Justice
Description: Prosecutor Holly Powell faces a murderous stalker after appearing on a true crime show to discuss her case against a corrupt judge she convicted, with the stalker believing the judge is innocent and seeking vengeance against Holly.

Title: Hot Spot
Description: It features three stories that are humorously evocative and a fourth one that's deeply disturbing.

Title: Holiday for Hire
Description: Dumped the day before taking him home for the Holidays, Katie hires a man to pretend to be her boyfriend for Christmas.

Title: Gandhi 3
Description: A local guy named Garry was called Gandhi and some referred to him as Robinhood in Punjab.

Title: The Summer We Died
Description: A group of young adults defy a curfew imposed due to a serial killer, documenting their nighttime adventures as they navigate the transition from adolescence to adulthood in the Nevada summer heat.

Title: Mustafar Takes Los Angeles: A Live Staged Reading of Star Wars: Episode III
Description: The Clone Wars climax as Anakin Skywalker, Obi-Wan Kenobi battle General Grievous, Count Dooku. Yoda, other Jedi face Darth Sidious while a sinister force looms, shaping Anakin's destiny.

Title: Pooja, Sir
Description: When two boys are kidnapped in a border town in Nepal, Detective Inspector Pooja is sent from Kathmandu to solve the case. But when she arrives, the brewing political unrest and violent protests throw her off course, and she is forced to seek help from Mamata, a local Madhesi policewoman. By putting aside systemic discrimination and pushing through everyday misogyny, the women solve the case - but at what personal cost? Inspired by real events which took place in Southern Nepal during the 2015 race protests.

Title: Silent Trees
Description: After her mom's tragic death on the Polish-Belarusian border a 16-year-old Kurdish girl Runa has to become a mother for her 4 younger brothers. A partially animated coming-of-age story in the times of a global refugee crisis.

Title: The Cellar
Description: A young girl wakes up imprisoned underground, with amnesia. She must escape, unravel the mystery behind her captivity, and confront her personal struggles. A suspenseful tale of survival, truth, and inner turmoil unfolds.

Title: The Chronicles of Libidoists
Description: Four individuals, adrift in their pursuit of sexual gratification, find themselves inextricably linked by a shared longing for a deeper, purer connection that transcends carnal desires.

Title: National Theatre Live: The Motive and the Cue
Description: Explores acting giants Burton and Gielgud staged Hamlet on Broadway in 1964.

Title: The Devil's Disciples
Description: The Devil's Disciples is a Horror, Fantasy, Mythological thriller.

Title: Empire Queen: The Golden Age of Magic
Description: In a kingdom where magic is forbidden, a charming trio of adventurers embark on a dangerous quest in search of the legendary Sovereign Wand, which is needed to overthrow an evil queen and restore magic for all.

Title: Fanatical: The Catfishing of Tegan and Sara
Description: Follows a catfishing scheme that targeted fans of the indie rock band Tegan and Sara, exploring the dark side of fandom.

Title: Paradise
Description: When corrupt officials cover up the murder of Ella's father, she cuts a swath through the anachronistic underbelly of her small island town.

Title: A Nanny's Revenge
Description: After hiring a seemingly innocuous nanny, a couple realizes she has sinister motives that threaten to destroy their family.

Title: Last Song for You
Description: A deceased woman gets a chance to reconnect with her past lover. They embark on a journey across time and continents to fulfill her wish of having her ashes scattered in Japan

Title: Rats!
Description: In Fresno, Texas, graffiti artist Raphael's arrest leads to his involvement in a chain of events involving a sting operation, suicide, drug deals, criminal suspicions, weapons, a newswoman, and a plutonium deal gone wrong, creating chaos.

Title: Psychonaut
Description: Enabled by a mysterious futuristic machine, Max, a young woman, dives inside the mind of her dying girlfriend, trying to find the essential memory that could save her life, all the while being hunted by a man they presumed to be dead.

Title: Off the Record
Description: LA musician Astor Grey seems to have it all - true love, a big break, and a hot rock star boyfriend - but in the cutthroat music industry, success and love come at a cost, and nothing is as perfect as it seems.

Title: Veni Vidi Vici
Description: The Maynards and their children lead an almost perfect billionaire family life. Amon is a passionate hunter, but doesn't shoot animals, as the family's wealth allows them to live totally free from consequences.

Title: Grassland
Description: Executive Produced by Academy Award Winner Common, Grassland is a riveting social justice thriller highlighting the perils of marijuana incarceration.

Title: Puntos suspensivos
Description: It follows Leo, an author. He is visited by a man claiming to be a journalist in a secret location where Leo is penning his next novel, but only his agent knows where he is.

Title: The Truth vs. Alex Jones
Description: Centers on families of the victims of the 2012 Sandy Hook shooting. They take Alex Jones, a conspiracy theorist, to court for spreading lies about the event being a hoax.

Title: Main Atal Hoon
Description: Follows the extraordinary life and political journey of Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee, an iconic figure in Indian politics and delves into the multifaceted persona of Vajpayee Ji, capturing his essence as a poet, a gentleman, and a statesman.

Title: Bhaiyya Ji
Description: A man who stands up for his family and seeks revenge for the wrongs done towards his loved ones.

Title: Simp
Description: A model gets kidnapped at a fake photo shoot. Based on true events.

Title: Land of Happiness
Description: In 1979 South Korea, a lawyer defends a secretary involved in the president's assassination, battling against predetermined military justice to ensure a fair trial amidst the nation's turmoil.

Title: The Severed Sun
Description: Magpie lives in an isolated church community ruled over by her father, The Pastor. When a man is murdered, paranoia sets in and people start to whisper about a strange 'Beast' that lives in the forest.

Title: Fool Me Once, Revenge on You
Description: Eartha Buckman, the heir to the most established corporation in Grimmington City, basks in the fairy tale romance with her boyfriend Kevin, only to find he's conspiring to kill her father and to swallow her family wealth. After surviving a hellish year in jail, Eartha comes out a brand-new woman with a vendetta, making Kevin lose everything he cares about. With the help of her best friend Claire and her new love, Scott, who just happens to be Kevin's right hand man, Eartha infiltrates Kevin's mind and business. Will she fulfill her revenge in this dangerous game of control she plays with her old flame and sworn enemy?

Title: Nedelja
Description: Life of Dzej Ramadanovski the popular Serbian folk singer.

Title: Do You Want to Die in Indio?
Description: Follows Salvi, a 17-year-old whose life gets complicated when his dreams are derailed by an enterprising drug dealer, an ethically challenged mentor, and a budding romance.

Title: Mond
Description: A former martial artist hired to train three wealthy Jordanian sisters finds her "dream job" turning unsettling as the isolated young women are under constant surveillance and show no interest in the sport. Why was she really hired?

Title: Restless
Description: A middle-aged empty nester's mundane life is upended when raucous new neighbors move in next door, unleashing potential danger and disruption.

Title: Ghosts of Red Ridge
Description: In the gold bust town of Red Ridge, a haunted Sheriff and his Deputy wrestle with outlaws causing chaos amid the town's decline.

Title: Stepmom from Hell
Description: Izzy's father's health fails. She suspects her stepmother and stepsister want his wealth. She uncovers embezzlement, corruption in the family business. Someone is willing to kill to protect secrets, putting Izzy's life at risk.

Title: My Divorce Party
Description: Divorcee Xan gathers her close friends to celebrate her impending split, only to reveal she intends to burn her divorce settlement money to start fresh. Chaos ensues as each friend has a wildly different opinion on what Xan should do.

Title: The Texas Cheerleader Murder Plot
Description: In 1991, Wanda Holloway was arrested for trying to hire a hit man to kill her daughter Shanna's cheerleading rival so that Shanna could get a place on the team. Now, Shanna reveals the truth behind what happened for the first time.

Title: Carnage for Christmas
Description: Lola, a true-crime podcaster, returns home for Christmas only to face a vengeful ghost reenacting the murders of a historical killer. With her community at risk, she must confront the town's buried secrets to stop the slaughter.

Title: Shayar
Description: Satta and Seero's enduring love faces obstacles from destiny. Their journey depicts the resilience of true passion as they strive to overcome adversity and be together

Title: Tanning Zone
Description: Two best friends working at an LA tanning salon question their life choices as former classmates achieve traditional success. Their dead-end job might just be genius - or the path to nowhere.

Title: Rita
Description: A seven year old Rita and her five year old brother Lolo from a working class family as the whole country goes crazy over the European football championships, with Spain in the quarter-finals.

Title: National Theatre Live: Nye
Description: Confronted with death, Aneurin 'Nye' Bevan's deepest memories lead him on a mind-bending journey back through his life; from childhood to mining underground, Parliament and fights with Churchill.

Title: Gharjwai
Description: A farmer's life intersects with a young woman and a mysterious stranger. As their secrets emerge, past connections surface and their fates become interlinked in a rural setting.

Title: My Ex's Wedding
Description: When groom invites his ex to the wedding, the ex and her partner, who are currently having relationship issues, attend to congratulate the bride and groom. However, complications arise when old flames reignite just before the wedding day.

Title: Tahong
Description: Mira is the daughter of a mussel farmer who needs to fight a reclamation project. She would do everything to save their livelihood even if it means sacrificing her innocence.

Title: Sadik Ahmet
Description: Adapted from a true story, this film is about the Dr. Sadik Ahmet, who fought for the democratic rights of Muslim Turks in Western Thrace for many years.

Title: We Work for the Dead
Description: If you're looking for a unique side hustle and don't mind being possessed...sign up for a delivery service with a dark twist. Your clients? The Dead.

Title: Charlotte
Description: Left alone with nowhere to go, Charlotte is picked up by an older man with questionable intentions.

Title: A New York Story
Description: A young woman risks being ostracized from an insular New York clique led by her socialite best friend when she falls for a charming photographer.

Title: L'orto americano
Description: A troubled young man falls for an American military auxiliary after a single glance. A year later, he moves to the American Midwest to write his novel, next to the auxiliary's elderly mother's house, separated by a grim garden.

Title: Kaulayaw
Description: Robb Guinto and Micaela Raz heat up the screen as college schoolmates who venture into the world of cybersex to support their needs. They fulfill their fans' sexual fantasy only to realized that they too, are falling for each other.

Title: Silence 2: The Night Owl Bar Shootout
Description: ACP Avinash Verma (Manoj Bajpayee) and his SCU are called upon by the Commissioner of Police to investigate a mass shoot-out at the Night Owl Bar in Mumbai. Layers begin to peel at something bigger, deeper, and darker at play.

Title: In His Own Image
Description: Antonia, a young Corsican photographer, navigates life, friendships, and love amidst the island's political turmoil from the 1980s to the early 2000s, depicting a generation's journey.

Title: Whisper of the Witch
Description: Mara, an ancient pagan spirit, hunts a group of teenagers taking their body parts to be reborn. A disillusioned and desperate investigator has to face his deepest fears to save the teenagers.

Title: Oru Kattil Oru Muri
Description: The film's narrative revolves around a bed and its three occupants. It follows Rugmangadan, who wakes up in his car and is pursued by goons, but.

Title: Ramnagar Bunny
Description: Reckless 21-year-old Bunny squanders his father's savings and juggles relationships. After a wake-up call, he faces a tough choice between love and responsibility in this Light-Hearted, emotional journey.

Title: U.S. Palmese
Description: In a desperate attempt to rebuild his reputation, a disgraced French soccer star reluctantly accepts a contract with an amateur team in Southern Italy

Title: The Binding
Description: Binyamin (21), moved to Tel aviv after coming as gay and facing the trauma after his brother death for which he feels responsible. Binyamin's life takes turn when his relationship with Avinoam (49), the pub owner he works, grows closer.

Title: Wisdom of Happiness
Description: Dalai Lama, talks directly to camera about inner peace, happiness, and potential for peaceful, happy 21st century.

Title: Throuple
Description: A lonely gay singer-songwriter learns how to ask for what he wants in life through a newfound romance with an honest and communicative married couple. All the while, he fears he is losing his best friend to her girlfriend.

Title: Dongeng Sang Kancil
Description: A mouse-deer, Sang Kancil, small in figure but cunning and wise. With his intelligence, Sang Kancil often escapes dangers and sometimes helps other animals that are in trouble with bigger and more fierce animals.

Title: Painter and Lampshade
Description: An artist meets a mysterious woman who becomes his model for his nude artwork. He then fantasizes making love to her; however, he always remembers her number one rule - she can't be touched.

Title: Double Ismart
Description: A notorious criminal with a terminal brain tumor hires a rogue scientist to transfer his mind into the body of a street-smart renegade with a unique memory transfer port in his brain.

Title: Spithood
Description: When a dangerous patient escapes confinement in a mental asylum and goes on a rampant killing spree, the night shift staff face their worst nightmare, as they fight for survival.

Title: Drowning Dry
Description: To celebrate Lukas' victory at the martial arts tournament and Tomas' birthday party, their wife's Juste and Ernesta organize a weekend at the summer house with a families. It was suppose to be a quiet weekend at countryside.

Title: Delicate Arch
Description: Four college kids with fracturing relationships take a camping trip in order to escape an ecological disaster. Alone in the desert, they begin to suspect that their reality might not be as it seems, and soon realize they're being watched.

Title: Troll Factory
Description: A crime drama that takes place when reporter Im Sang-jin, who learned of the existence of the 'comment army' through a report on online public opinion manipulation, encounters a huge entity in the process of covering them.

Title: Babydoll
Description: Meet Babydoll. She's desperate to spend her birthday with the man she loves. It just so happens that he's also her boss.

Title: Neshoma
Description: Neshoma is set in Amsterdam between World War I & II, when one out of ten of the city's residents was Jewish. Seventeen-year-old Rusha lives in the Jewish quarter with her family. Her older brother Max has emigrated to the Dutch East Indies, now Indonesia. In her letters to Max, Rusha recounts daily life in the city. This creates a vivid image of Amsterdam during the interwar period, from the perspective of the Jewish community. The film begins shortly after World War I, a period full of confidence in the future. The combination of Rusha's letters and archival footage creates a colorful portrait of proud diamond cutters; haggling traders at the flea market; cabaret artists with songs that everyone sings along to; city officials like De Miranda, who are committed to social housing; and the entrepreneurs behind warehouse De Bijenkorf, the luxurious Amstel Hotel, and cinema Tuschinski. These stories illustrate the importance of the Jewish community to the city. The initial optimism after World War I is gradually tested by a severe economic depression and the rise of fascism, leading to the occupation of The Netherlands. Humor and zest for life, the "lechajim," provide comfort to the Jews in times of adversity. Against this backdrop, Rusha grows from a young girl into an independent woman, lovingly navigating between the ideas of her socialist father and the religious beliefs of her husband. The outbreak of World War II presents her with an impossible choice. Neshoma is not only about the lives of those who are no longer here, but also about what they have left behind: the Jewish soul of Amsterdam, the neshoma.

Title: Rode College
Description: When an intelligence officers steps into the world of Rode College, student leaders turn against a corrupt politician who has been manipulating the college's youth for two generations for his own political gains. Inspired from True Events.

Title: The Window
Description: Mina, a 15-year-old Pakistani girl, is given as atonement for her brother's misdeed. Her ruthless spouse imprisons her, leaving her imagination as refuge, while their families' lives collide in a devastating manner.

Title: Crocodile Tears
Description: An overbearing mother who lives with her son in a secluded crocodile farm spirals out of control when her son sees the outside world and falls for a girl for the first time.

Title: A Circus Tale & a Love Song
Description: Refugio, a romantic dreamer whose years long quest to find true love takes him from the circus life in Mexico to the nightlife of New Orleans, where he unexpectedly falls for a beautiful exotic dancer with a complicated past and a dangerous ex-lover who refuses to let her go.

Title: Sketch
Description: Still reeling from the unexpected loss of his wife, a single dad (Hale) navigates uncharted territory when his daughter's comically dark, scribbled drawings begin to come to life and wreak havoc on their small town.

Title: Purgatory Station
Description: When a crooked lawyer wakes up in a large, pitch-dark container, he learns he has eight hours to scuttle a corporate land grab or see everyone he loves die horribly. .

Title: Do You See What I See
Description: On her birthday, Mawar's dream, who was lonely and only accompanied by her boarding house friends, came true about the partner she dreamed of. However, after finding this partner, Mawar's behavior became increasingly strange.

Title: In Vitro
Description: On a struggling cattle farm some years in the future, a woman discovers the unsettling consequences of her husband's animal breeding technology.

Title: Death Streamer
Description: A modern-day vampire employs technologically advanced glasses that enable him to hunt and LIVE STREAM his bloody feasts.

Title: Butchers Book Three: Bonesaw
Description: In this third installment of the Butchers Series, three women find themselves being hunted by a vicious killer who slaughters people and hacks them up in his van, while a clever sheriff pieces together the clues he's leaving behind.

Title: Art of Eight Limbs
Description: A US agent goes undercover at a martial arts training camp which is suspected of being a cover for chemical weapons.

Title: Babah
Description: As Isyak and his daughter Maya face the ups and downs of life, from losing a job to battling illness and the loss of hearing, their strong bond reveals the enduring power of love and family to carry them through the toughest times.

Title: Mahal Ko Ang Mahal Mo
Description: Two women hurt by the same man form an alliance to catch their womanizer boyfriend in the act. But their unexpected bond leads to an unlikely romance between them.

Title: The Flats
Description: Joe and his Belfast neighbors reenact childhood memories from the violent Troubles era in their Catholic district, exploring the collective experiences that shaped their lives and community.

Title: The Last Nightmare Part One
Description: Part One to the epic finale of the H20 story. Sequel to The Haddonfield Nightmare (2021)

Title: All About the Levkoviches
Description: A generous and stubborn elderly boxing coach who gets along with everyone except his own son. They're reunited after the death of the old man's wife and forced to face old grievances.

Title: Unspoken
Description: A grieving Chinese father travels to America to collect his daughter and stays to catch the killer.

Title: Once in a Valentine
Description: After falling for a man who proposes quickly, a woman learns he's the stranger who assaulted her years ago, upending her future.

Title: About a Hero
Description: The film mixes artificial intelligence and the work of German filmmaker Werner Herzog, with a screenplay generated by AI.

Title: Fighting the Fire
Description: Brian Cook has been firefighter for over 15 years, but he is now facing the biggest battle of his life - not the fire in the field, but the fire burning inside.

Title: A Good Man 2
Description: Trying to start a better life, a man after leaving a trail of his past finds a woman that's no better than the last one he left and pays the ultimate price

Title: Bloody Beggar
Description: A beggar's life takes an unexpected turn when a misadventure upends his daily routine. Can he navigate the bizarre, witty situations that follow?

Title: The Stalking
Description: A witch conjures up evil spirits in the form of malignant sunflower plants which wreak havoc on a small suburban town. And a group of bullied teens must fight to survive these and other terrors that await them on Halloween Night.

Title: Family Secrets: The Disappearance of Alissa Turney
Description: Sarah Turney became a viral sensation when she posted suspicions on social media that her dad killed her sister, Alissa. Now Sarah, re-examines her and Alissa's childhood.

Title: 11 Rebels
Description: Amidst the Boshin War's brutal conflicts, a motley squad of criminals and samurai undertakes a desperate defense of a fortress, their stand triggered by clashing interests of the Shibata clan, the shogunate, and the new government.

Title: Simon of the Mountain
Description: Seeking change, 21-year-old Simon finds purpose by befriending two disabled children who teach him to embrace life's joys. Together, they navigate a world not designed for them, inventing their own rules for love and happiness.

Title: Ayalaan
Description: A lost alien seeks help to go back to his home, but everything gets harder after the alien returns to its home.

Title: Les arènes
Description: At just 18 years old, Brahim, a promising young footballer, is preparing to realize his dream: signing his first professional contract in Lyon, his club, his city. But the emergence within the club of a powerful foreign agent reshuffles the cards. With Mehdi, his cousin and agent, Brahim embarks on a race against time on the transfer market, "the transfer window", where anything goes.

Title: The Infallibles
Description: While a gang of robbers has been sowing chaos in Paris and humiliating the police for months, the Minister of the Interior wants new blood to head the investigation: Alia, explosive and unmanageable, Hugo, valedictorian and meticulous.

Title: Missing
Description: A girl vanishes while walking, leaving her family devastated. As months pass without clues, rumors about her mother's actions intensify online, straining her marriage.

Title: Vanilla Ice Cream
Description: Varun and Komal, college lovers, marry against families' wishes. Navigating responsibilities, values, freedom, their relationship faces misunderstandings, testing togetherness amidst rights and wrongs.

Title: Ship of the Damned
Description: After an abandoned 500 year-old ship appears off the coast of a small town, Historian Elena and the local coastguard go to investigate. They discover it is not abandoned and the ship's cursed crew have horrific plans for the intruders.

Title: Conquer: Lahad Datu
Description: The Malaysian security forces in quelling the militant group of the Sulu Sultanate aka "Operation Daulat" in Lahad Datu, Sabah.

Title: Listen Carefully
Description: When troubled assistant bank manager Andy McNeary's baby daughter goes missing, he must follow the instructions of a mysterious voice on the other end of a baby monitor to save her before she disappears forever.

Title: Unfruitful Times
Description: After a tragic miscarriage, Nimet -a middle aged woman- gets stuck in the conservative society in Istanbul while her beloved younger sister Öznur carries a burden of her own in the family, trying to struggle her own demons.

Title: Broken Bird
Description: Sybil works at an undertakers. It's a lonely job, with few perks. So she takes solace where she can.

Title: WWII: Operation Phoenix
Description: A small group of Allied commandos must parachute into enemy occupied Europe and recover the information a female spy was carrying, at all costs. They soon realize that this would be the easy part of the mission.

Title: Dilan 1983
Description: In 1983, Dilan reunites with his elementary school friends after a year and a half away and tries to impress a transfer student.

Title: Red Flag
Description: Gina, a car saleswoman, starts dating Red, a coworker with a reputation for womanizing. Their intense romance progresses quickly, but doubts surface about Red's intentions and potential warning signs.

Title: Gacy: Serial Killer Next Door
Description: A teenager's life in a quiet suburb changes drastically when John Wayne Gacy, a famed serial killer, becomes his neighbor. His curiosity leads to dark secrets and a frightening journey from innocence to a dire clash with evil.

Title: Heretics
Description: Recovered footage documents the horror of a group of teens who break into the abandoned Simmons House. What begins as a thrill-seeking adventure turns into a nightmare as they discover a dark cult intent on sacrificing them one by one.

Title: Campton Manor
Description: An author tries to investigate a decades old mystery and finds himself stuck in his own ghost story.

Title: Monkey on a Stick
Description: Monkey on a Stick is a feature-length documentary exposé of the criminal activity that took place in and around the Hare Krishna movement in America in the 1970s and '80s, adapted from the New York Times bestselling book.

Title: The Great Warning
Description: This documentary chronicles the fact finding research of an unprecedented apocalyptic event in our earth. It's explored through the lenses of science, history, and spirituality.

Title: Rent Free
Description: After hitting emotional and financial rock bottom, best friends Ben and Jordan come up with a scheme to spend an entire year living "rent free" with the help of friends, family and strangers alike in a rapidly changing Austin.

Title: Kaka Boss
Description: Centers on a ruthless debt collector experiencing a change of heart and pursuing his passion for singing.

Title: Aiden
Description: In a desperate bid for survival, Aiden flees the suffocating grip of domestic violence and seeks refuge in a remote cabin, where unconventional therapy sessions force him to confront his past, which opens an intriguing twist.

Title: Captain Miller
Description: A man leaves and turns against the British-led Indian military after witnessing atrocity.

Title: Diciannove
Description: A curious student embarks on a journey of self-discovery, learning that the path, no matter how unfamiliar or daunting, is worthwhile.

Title: The Partisan
Description: A Polish spy who works for the British during the Second World War. After a betrayal, she is compromised in Warsaw and finds herself in a murky world of treachery.

Title: High Forces
Description: Gao Haojun, an international security expert, is hijacked by gunmen on the first flight of A380 airliner, and his blind daughter is one of the undercover hostages, a fact that he doesn't know.

Title: I Heart Robots
Description: Years after a robot apocalypse, Terra ventures away from her secluded compound to take her lovable robot companion West to save what's left of a dying world.

Title: Spilt Milk
Description: 11 year-old boy dreams of becoming a great detective like his TV hero Kojak. He sets up a private investigation with his best friend, but the disappearance of his older brother sets them off down a dark path.

Title: Alter weißer Mann
Description: Heinz Heimlich fulfills the cliche of the the so called old white man. In order to get promoted, he pretends to be political correct. But the facade begins to falter when he invites his superiors to his house for dinner one day.

Title: The Way We Speak
Description: An up-and-coming writer refuses to leave the spotlight when his best friend and debate opponent suffers cardiac arrest, leading to an obsession over his new opponent and a growing rift with his ailing wife.

Title: Chris Brown: A History of Violence
Description: Explore the biographical film that delves into the controversial personal life of Chris Brown, an iconic singer while exploring allegations of domestic violence, assault charges and sexual misconduct.

Title: Regarding Us
Description: Fired from her teaching job at a Catholic school, a transgender woman contemplates suicide until she meets a young girl with two fathers, and they have a profound impact on each other's lives.

Title: ABBA: Against the Odds
Description: To commemorate the 50th anniversary of the iconic Swedish group winning the Eurovision Song Contest.

Title: Don't Let's Go to the Dogs Tonight
Description: Depicts 8-year-old Bobo's life on her family's Rhodesian farm during the Bush War's final stages. It explores the family's bond with Africa's land and the war's impact on the region and individuals through Bobo's perspective.

Title: Bogart: Life Comes in Flashes
Description: Explores the iconic actor's journey to stardom through his relationships with his mother and four wives, including Lauren Bacall, using rare footage and his own narration to offer an intimate portrait of a deserving star.

Title: Winter Island
Description: When a young girl is found dead on a small, wooded island, her teenage brother's postmortem visions point to an evil presence within their own family.

Title: Chhatrapati Sambhaji
Description: Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj, son of Shivaji Maharaj, who grew up without parental love. Sambhaji proved himself a fearless and brave ruler, winning battles and instilling fear in the Mughal Empire.

Title: Vittoria
Description: A woman's world turns upside down after her father's death, as she experiences a recurring dream of a little girl, compelling her to dive into international adoption, risking her marriage, family stability, and moral compass.

Title: Rokjesnacht
Description: Neurotic Jenny and number-cruncher Bob are hell-bent on dating. When they are unexpectedly matched via a new dating platform, matchmaker Roos tries to show Bob and Jenny that despite their differences, they are the perfect match.

Title: Alterlove
Description: Paris, Present day. On a fleeting night, two strangers embark on a spontaneous romantic adventure that challenges their views on love and connection, blending humor and heartfelt moments in a unique exploration of modern relationships.

Title: Addy Daddy
Description: A lonely young man introduces his new girlfriend to his parents and they immediately hate her for no reason.

Title: I Am Martin Parr
Description: Since the 1970s, Martin Parr has held up a sometimes tender, sometimes critical and always mischievous mirror to our times. Through this intimate road trip across England, discover the men who revolutionized contemporary photography.

Title: Deadly Invitations
Description: An influencer comes across a VIP party invite not meant for her and dives headfirst into the side of the industry where secrets are worth killing for.

Title: Emakku Thozhil Romance
Description: Assistant director Umashankar falls for Leo. Misunderstanding arises when Saranya gets pregnant by Prashant. Leo blames Umashankar, causing rift between them.

Title: Eternal You
Description: Startups use AI to create avatars that allows to talk with their loved ones after death. Exploration of deep human desire for immortality, questioning consequences of commodifying this age-old dream.

Title: No Pressure
Description: After being tricked into dropping everything to save her grandmother's farm, big-city chef Oliwia falls for a handsome farmer who's hiding a secret.

Title: Switch Up
Description: A man's world gets turned upside down and he finds himself stranded at a homeless shelter, where he meets a young widow. He begins to fall in love and to understand how helping others is the true path to finding happiness.

Title: Holy Electricity
Description: When young Gonga and his cousin Bart find a suitcase full of rusty crosses in a scrapyard, Bart gets the idea to turn them into neon crucifixes and sell them door-to-door to the gullible inhabitants of Tbilisi. Their crusade through the suburbs of the city becomes a quest for love and friendship.

Title: Tell That to the Winter Sea
Description: Just a week before Jo gets married, she is reunited with Scarlet, rekindling their friendship and an ex-teen romance.

Title: Possession Street
Description: When seven malevolent spirits are unleashed to possess the tenants of a dying mall, it falls to a jaded ex-stuntman, his headstrong daughter and a washed-up Daoist priest to stop the undead before they spread onto the streets beyond.

Title: Bis Repetita
Description: Delphine, a disillusioned literature teacher, has a deal with her pupils: they leave her in peace and she gives them 19/20 marks. But the deal backfires when her fictitious results send her class to the world Latin championship in Naples.

Title: Pujar Sarki
Description: Three individuals unite against societal norms perpetuating caste discrimination, facing challenges in their collective struggle to defy the existing caste-based social order.

Title: Some Rain Must Fall
Description: Cai, a housewife who seems to have lost track of who she is and who she wants to be. During her daughter's basketball matches, she hurts an elderly woman. This event turns out to be a catalyst for a life that is spinning out of control.

Title: FanGirl
Description: A popular influencer hosts a contest for her fans, with the grand prize being a day spent with her. But one woman devises a plan: kill the winner, impersonate her, and get close to the influencer to ultimately kill her.

Title: Then Chennai
Description: Jason gets caught in a standoff between security forces and a gang. He fights to protect his loved ones while chaos consumes his life.

Title: Ciao bambino
Description: At the end of the summer of his nineteen years Attilio, a boy who lives in a working-class neighborhood of Naples, is tasked with protecting a young prostitute from the East. Attilio, without being able to openly admit it, falls in love with her. However, when his father is released from prison and is forced to repay a substantial debt, Attilio finds himself choosing between his love for the girl and his love for his father, putting his freedom and his life up to that point at stake.

Title: Possessions
