Description: Danny, an ex-soldier homeless in Dublin, meets Will, a teen fleeing a drug gang. Their encounter forces them to confront their pasts while navigating the harsh realities they face.

Title: Kaam Chalu Hai
Description: A father channels his pain into a revolutionary movement, while cherishing his small, happy world with his daughter Gudiya and wife Radha. His mission is to fulfill Gudiya's dream of becoming a cricketer.

Title: Sayen: The Huntress
Description: Sayen joins a clandestine resistance group with a plan involving Valerie, who will provide needed information in exchange for her freedom. The rescue operation pushes Sayen to extremes limits, leading to a final confrontation.

Title: Housewife of the Year
Description: Former contestants of the Housewife of the Year competition tell the story of a resilient generation of women, and how they changed a country. Winner of Best Irish Feature Documentary at the Galway Film Fleadh 2024.

Title: Peter Rabid
Description: Will any of the former school pals survive? Will anything remain of them after Peter Rabid and his insane sister Bedelia lure them to a secluded country home and start killing them one by one? A sinister cult is controlling the killers.

Title: Estômago II: O Poderoso Chef
Description: Nonato, with his food, won over the powerful in the hierarchy of the prison where he is serving his sentence. But the arrival of a famous Italian mobster will shake the structures and place the chef at the epicenter of a power struggle.

Title: Familiar Touch
Description: An octogenarian woman transitions to life in assisted living as she contends with her conflicting relationship to herself and her caregivers amidst her shifting memory, age identity, and desires.

Title: Mongrel
Description: Oom has no papers or formal training but is good at caring for the elderly and disabled. When his situation as a caregiver in the mountains becomes too much for him, he has to choose between survival or dignity.

Title: Trust in Love
Description: Record producer Mickey Ferrara, struggling with career, marriage, and relationship with his family, slowly learns to recover them all.

Title: Udan Chhoo
Description: Udan Chhoo is a Gujarati Movie starring Deven Bhojani, Prachee Shah Paandya, Aarohi and Aarjav Trivedi in prominent roles.

Title: Global Harmony
Description: It dives deep into the world of high-stakes journalism and global justice. Award-winning journalist Richard Foster abandons his family's lucrative business empire to create the Global Harmony Foundation, a beacon for equality and unification. As Foster and his dedicated team gear up for an unprecedented global conference, their mission is jeopardized by a formidable crime ring with its own sinister agenda. Tensions escalate as ideals clash with dark realities, moral dilemmas, and unexpected twists.

Title: Athomugam
Description: Playful act of Martin by installing a spy app in his love of life Leena's phone reveals a mysterious character thereby triggering events that questions love,trust, friendship, technology and unravels the thrilling darkside of human actions

Title: Jatt & Juliet 3
Description: Two police officers from Punjab travel to London on a mission that proves more complicated than expected.

Title: Enescu, Skinned Alive
Description: George Enescu, a brilliant composer and violinist, is at the peak of his career and wants to compose an opera. He falls in love with a princess, Maruca, who inspires and challenges him. She is fascinated by Enescu and his music.

Title: Guilty Pleasure
Description: Guilty Pleasure explores the complex relationships and personal struggles of three ambitious lawyers as they navigate their way through love, betrayal, and ambition.

Title: Summer Rain
Description: The alluring sounds of violin music bring back memories that reunite a father and daughter separated at birth. Though neither realized what had happened in the past, they were drawn to each other unmistakably when they do meet.

Title: Shark Island
Description: Beautiful models travel to a tropical island for a bikini photo shoot with a priceless necklace. But a killer is loose on this remote island and the only way out is through shark-infested waters.

Title: Bed & Breakfast
Description: A socially awkward workaholic resigns on a whim and then contemplates her new future in a Groningen village full of eccentrics while wrapping the local bachelors around her finger.

Title: Canvas
Description: Follows an ex-child art prodigy as she is harrowed by her sister who returns to their childhood home and tries to get her committed.

Title: Rock 'n' Roll Ringo
Description: A scaffolding builder loses his job and starts as a temporary worker at the funfair. There he is seduced by a showman into making a career as a fairground boxer - and hopes to fulfill a long-awaited dream for his daughter.

Title: Blood Mountain Massacre
Description: The Blood Mountain Massacre follows an ambitious all-girl punk band on tour, stalked by an escaped psychopath.

Title: Mountain Shark
Description: A skilled group of hunters are sent out into the dark mysterious mountains surrounding a weapons research base on a secret mission and soon learn the deadly truth that waits for them, as the hills are alive with the sound of screaming.

Title: Veeranjaneyulu Vihara Yatra
Description: A dysfunctional family sets off on a road trip to immerse the grandfather's ashes in Goa and drama ensues.

Title: 8 Views of Lake Biwa
Description: On the shimmering shores of Europe's otherworldly edge, two teenage girls, Hanake and her best friend are discussing their first love interest while gazing out at yachts sailing to Kyoto. They whisper prayers and poems, the language of their longings. But the magic is fading in their isolated fishing village as they come to terms with a recent disaster, with some indulging in acts of erotic art, some in spiritual spells. It becomes clear that intimacy alone won't help them process their loss. In a deeply visceral tale, acclaimed Estonian director Marko Raat explores themes of love, illuminating the lives of a community who still believe that they are connected to the universe.

Title: Road Wars: Max Fury
Description: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, two sisters leave their stronghold to save their wounded mother. Armed only with a muscle car and limited ammo, they race against ruthless raiders to secure lifesaving supplies from a distant outpost.

Title: Sengkolo: Malam satu suro
Description: In Javanese culture, Sengkolo is a negative entity that often haunts humans, brings bad luck and brings disaster. On the first night of Suro, Sengkolo moved to target several weton who were his prey.

Title: Milano
Description: Alain is raising his son Milano on his own. Determined to make their future better, he tries to make ends meet.

Title: Love You as the World Ends Final
Description: Utopia was a tower of hope, but it was a tower of despair created by human desires. In Utopia, they were researching the only way to save this world: a vaccine against the monster called Golem. One girl with special antibodies was used as research material. Her name is Mirai, the daughter of Hibiki Mamiya. Hibiki decides to rescue Mirai together with five men who have gathered in Utopia. The men are trying to rescue their loved ones, to save their family and friends, and to steal food and money to survive. Although each of them has their own non-negotiables and some rebellion, they gradually come to resonate with Hibiki's beliefs and decide to fight together.

Title: Kapalit
Description: Audrey is hired as a private nurse by Stan for his sick wife, Demi. But as Audrey spends time with the married couple, she falls for Stan and works her way to replace Demi as Stan's lover.

Title: Cup
Description: The story of a sixteen-year-old boy, a badminton player from a village named Vellathooval in Idukki, who dreams of the Olympics.

Title: Too Little Too Late
Description: Boss Honcho faces betrayal from ex-lover Rain, his business partner who schemes to overthrow him. As she plots to seize control, their power struggle puts both their empire and lives at risk.

Title: Killjoy: Terrify
Description: When a secret society of Voodoo priestesses resurrect a centuries-old chaos demon and unleash him on the hood, they prove that you can't keep a good clown down. When the mischievous Killjoy starts playing by his own rules, however, the women learn that all their witchcraft cannot contain the malevolent spirit they have unleashed.

Title: Sambavami Yuge Yuge
Description: Young Arjun, the village panchayat president, clashes with the new DC over differing leadership styles, putting the village's progress at stake.

Title: The Worst Man in London
Description: Charles Augustus Howell was John Ruskin's secretary, agent and model for Dante Gabriel Rossetti, and exhumer of Lizzie Siddal. But he is also said to have been a master blackmailer and a forger of works of art.

Title: Ghamasaan
Description: A cat-and-mouse tale set in the Hindi heartland, where male friendships and rivalries unveil homoerotic tensions. Men on both sides of the law traverse arid lands, creating a sense of place where unexplored histories reside.

Title: I Hate I Love You
Description: Jacinda and Bradley, media company partners, face betrayal and illegal activities amid success. Motives drive agendas, jeopardizing love and business. Navigating friendships and enemies becomes crucial for survival.

Title: XiXi
Description: Through intimate video diaries, it explores intergenerational wounds and challenges social values' impact on existence. By sharing personal journeys, it offers a mirror to reflect on struggles and vulnerability when forging one's path.

Title: Bolero
Description: A woman travels through dimensions to find a distant man.

Title: Virgo
Description: The young punk band "The Rasperries" is touring Sweden in a worn-out van. Along the way, they meet Ava, a charming and intense goth girl who offers them an after-party - while pursuing a dark agenda of her own.

Title: Twisted Marriage
Description: Two married couples who have been long-time friends decide to swap partners for a weekend, leading to lots of questions and jealousy.

Title: Un/Happy for You
Description: Chef Juancho reunites with ex-girlfriend Zy, visiting hometown. Initially seeking revenge against her engagement, he unexpectedly redevelops feelings.

Title: My Future You
Description: This is a magical story of 2 people, Lex and Karen, from different timelines - 13 years apart - connected by a mysterious comet through a dating app. As they grow close, Karen asks Lex to change key moments in her past to prevent her parents' separation. But every change of the past brings unforeseen consequences, altering their futures in unexpected ways. In one last effort, Lex hopes to set things right, but some events may be beyond control.

Title: Played and Betrayed
Description: While on vacation in the UK, a complacent husband and wife find themselves drawn toward a fiery couple who secretly have sinister intentions.

Title: Matt Rife: Lucid - A Crowd Work Special
Description: In Netflix's first-ever crowd work special, Matt Rife gets up close and personal with an unpredictable Charlotte audience to riff on all things dreams.

Title: Crosspoint
Description: A washed-up Filipino actor and struggling entertainer in Japan, Manuel Hidalgo comes across a high-profile serial killer at large with a bankrupt businessman Shigeru Yamaguchi.

Title: Algiers
Description: The kidnapping of a little girl creates tension and suspicion in Algiers. Only Dounia, a brilliant psychiatrist, and Sami, a police inspector, can unearth the demons of the past.

Title: Je le jure
Description: Marco, in his thirties, goes through life without a compass. Employee of a recycling center in Forbach, in Lorraine, he finds comfort in alcohol. And a little with Madeleine, a mature woman with whom he secretly has a relationship. One day, he is drawn by lot to be a juror of Assisi. He a little dropped, incapable of discernment for himself, will have to decide the life of a young arsonist, accused of manslaughter.

Title: Okie
Description: Louie, an acclaimed writer, returns to his hometown after his father's death. Confronted with a host of people from his past, Louie is forced to reconcile with the stories he's stolen, misrepresented, or downright exploited for profit.

Title: Guardians
Description: A charismatic preacher works with guardian angels to save two young women from life-threatening decisions.

Title: The Ark and the Darkness
Description: Noah's Ark withstands a global flood, corroborated by scientific evidence across disciplines. A team exposes the truth behind this ancient tale found in cultures worldwide, confirming the Biblical account.

Title: Ambajipeta Marriage Band
Description: In a small village during the early 2000s, happy twins Mallikarjuna and Padmavati find their lives changing on their 25th birthday.

Title: Megdan: Between Water and Fire
Description: A former martial artist faces a moral dilemma from his past as his career winds down. A group grapples with having to choose between conflicting desires.

Title: Night of the Skinwalkers
Description: Four couples stranded at a remote lakeside cabin on the eve of a reported alien invasion discover not everything is as it seems.

Title: Princesa Adormecida
Description: Rosa's overprotective uncles shield her from a hidden truth. At fifteen, a mystery from the past emerges, endangering Rosa amidst a villain's vengeance, forcing her to confront the reality she believed was mere fantasy.

Title: Proslava
Description: A young Croatian villager's innocence is shattered by the harsh realities of war, deprivation, and political turmoil between 1926 and 1945, leading him down a dark path.

Title: Bandaa Singh Chaudhary
Description: Set during 1971 Indo-Pak war's aftermath, communal riots in Punjab. A man fights for rights, family's survival amid division, violence. An ordinary man fights to protect his family's rights and survive amidst deep divisions and violence.

Title: Mary Anning & the Dinosaur Hunters
Description: Mary Anning - preeminent pioneering 19th-century Jurassic fossil hunter strives for recognition and equality in a patriarchal society. To this day she remains widely unknown despite highly influencing Darwin's theory of evolution.

Title: The People Before
Description: Eerie psychological thriller set in the Suffolk countryside.

Title: Omo nero e Bucefalo in Kurdistan iracheno
Description: A man and a motorbike who together traveled more than half a million kilometers to discover Iraqi Kurdistan.

Title: Art of a Hit
Description: With their careers on the line, a late-90s rock band journeys to a French chateau to record with an elusive super-producer. But as tensions rise and tempers flare, they realize they're up against more than just the pressure to succeed.

Title: Pretty Boys
Description: Grey is a flamboyant and charming twink, and his longtime best friend is Jonas, a heartthrob with a masculine appeal. While Jonas effortlessly navigates the gay dating scene, Grey struggles to find love.

Title: Hit List
Description: Vijay's family is kidnapped by a masked assailant. He's forced to assassinate the kidnapper's rivals as part of a twisted revenge plot. As Vijay complies, he unravels the kidnapper's identity and motives.

Title: Lagan Special
Description: Shekhar and Suman's arranged marriage hits a snag when she overhears him admitting he doesn't love her. Calling off the ceremony, families argue while Shekhar tries convincing Suman of his devotion.

Title: Exorcism Chronicles: The Beginning
Description: A doctor-turned-priest, Father Park was excommunicated for performing exorcisms by a church that refused to believe in the supernatural beings preying on the innocent. When his long-time friend, a monk from a secretive and magic-wielding temple, calls upon him to protect a naïve yet powerful child from his corrupt master, Father Park must face his inner demons to rescue the boy or risk repeating the same tragedy that he took up the cross to prevent.

Title: Netting the Waters
Description: The history of fishing for pickerel, perch and smelt on the Great Lakes, includes rarely seen footage of activities on the fishing tugs, plus candid opinions about the future of the industry.

Title: GG
Description: GG, an acronym for "good game," centers around Seth, a determined aspiring gamer who immerses himself in the world of video games who gets into a "competitive barkada gaming" while navigating the various challenges within his own family.

Title: Petta Rap
Description: "PETTA RAP" tells the love journey of BALA (a middle class man whose ambition is to become the best action hero of Tamil movies.) and JANAKI (a local girl, who becomes a Pop Singer.)

Title: The Good Loan Sharks
Description: Two brothers ordered by their father to leave the house and live independently. So they opened a money-lending company to survive. However, an existing competitor is not happy and tries to ruin their business.

Title: Christmas in Lagos
Description: During festive Detty December, four friends navigate love, heartbreak, and cultural expectations. Fiyin's feelings complicated by Elo's fiancée. Gbemi juggles boyfriend and ex. Ivie caught off guard by vacation fling with Ajani.

Title: Blade of Fury
Description: Knife catcher Pei Xing originally exchanged his life for money as bounty hunter, but after witnessing the killing of people who stood up for justice, he gradually awakened and decided to fight back.

Title: How to Kiss a Girl
Description: A lonely mistress falls for her neighbor and fellow mistress, igniting a passionate affair. Meanwhile, two women betrayed by the same man join forces to catch him in the act, only to find love in each other.

Title: Miss Boots
Description: When an orphaned girl loses her grandmother, her uncle, a one hit wonder opera composer, needs to take care of her until a foster family is found, while also struggling to finish his next big hit.

Title: Huntress
Description: In the grim final days of WWII, German soldiers and civilians will do anything to survive. An army medical team is on the run, trapped behind enemy lines as they are hunted by a vicious killer bent on their total annihilation.

Title: Followers
Description: A year after surviving a brutal attack, a social media influencer and her friends find themselves once again in the crosshairs of a dangerous and relentless dark web cult, thirsting for retribution and willing to stop at nothing to get it.

Title: Fureru
Description: Aki, Ryo, and Yuta, childhood friends who grew up on the same island, are 20 years old and start living together in Takadanobaba, Tokyo. Even though their living environments are different: they work part-time at a bar, work as salespeople at a real estate company, and are students at a vocational school for clothing designers, the three are always connected in their hearts. The reason is, the mysterious creatures brought from the island, Touch, have mysterious powers similar to telepathy that connect them with different hobbies and personalities. The friendship between the three should continue, but they discover another hidden power of touch..

Title: Horrible
Description: The 2nd part of the film "Thorn" based on a life story of a publicly known pop folk singer in Serbia - Aca Lukas. The second part deals with his days in prison, going out under suspicious circumstances, paying back gambling debts and trying to get treatment for all kinds of addictions. At the same time, great popularity and the burden of elite life, where everything is available to him, make his personal path difficult.

Title: Five Friends
Description: Trapped on Mount Madyopuro because they violated a myth, Bagas, Lenni, Dicky, Juna and Andrew became suspicious of each other that one of them was a ghost.

Title: Salisihan
Description: When a childless couple lets a pregnant woman inside their home, temptation starts to shake their once peaceful life.

Title: Lohusa
Description: Lohusa tells the funny story of a mother and father trying to keep up with life during the first 40 days after birth.

Title: Once Upon a Time in Madras
Description: A gun that is accidentally discovered, and what happens because of that to four different characters and their lives.

Title: Marni: The Story of Wewe Gombel
Description: One family, namely Rahayu and her two children, Anissa and Aan, moved to a village that is said to have a dark history. One day, Aan disappeared without a trace because he was kidnapped by a spirit.

Title: The House on Laura Anne Dr.
Description: A young couple move to Florida for a fresh start only to realize their new home has something sinister lurking.

Title: Elementary
Description: A documentary that unveils the profound impact of teachers' devotion to their students. Witness their daily triumphs and struggles as they inspire young minds with unwavering dedication.

Title: Zero
Description: Two Americans end up in Dakar, Senegal with bombs strapped to their chests and ten hours to find out why.

Title: Larger Than Life: Reign of the Boybands
Description: Tracing boy bands' evolution from The Beatles to K-pop, delving into the 90s/2000s icons and highlighting this enduring musical movement's rich history.

Title: Michelle Buteau: A Buteau-ful Mind at Radio City Music Hall
Description: Michelle Buteau talks going viral, raising twins, and the lows of getting high in this herstory-making special.

Title: Kemba
Description: The film follows criminal justice reform advocate Kemba Smith, a woman charged as a co-conspirator to her college boyfriend's drug-trafficking crimes and sentenced to 24.5 years in federal prison with no opportunity for parole.

Title: Pig at the Crossing
Description: Dolom, a YouTuber, has an affair with married Deki. She's pregnant. After his accidental death, Dolom's soul enters limbo. Guided to confront his past choices, he must relinquish attachments to move on or remain trapped indefinitely.

Title: An Open Door: Temple Grandin
Description: Acclaimed documentary celebrating Dr. Temple Grandin's pioneering work in animal welfare, autism advocacy, and neurodiversity through her unique perspective as a visual thinker on the autism spectrum.

Title: Married to a Balla
Description: When a mother suffering from domestic abuse escapes her dangerous, pro-athlete husband, she will stop at nothing to keep her family safe.

Title: Mrs. Robinson
Description: Explores the life and career of Mary Robinson, a pioneering constitutional lawyer, the first female President of Ireland, the UN's High Commissioner for Human Rights and the Chair of The Elders.

Title: The Collaborator
Description: As war rages, a young man from a nearby village is recruited by an army officer to perform a grim task, to go into the conflict zone where militants have been killed and retrieve their weapons and ID cards.

Title: Blue Sun Palace
Description: When tragedy strikes, an unexpected bond forms between two migrants in the Chinese community of Queens. Far from home, their labor-filled lives intertwine as they grieve and search for familial connections.

Title: My Redneck Neighbor: Chapter 1 - The Rednecks Are Coming
Description: Crazy Asians collide with a bunch of Insane Rednecks who move into an Hollywood Hillside to set up

Title: Blue
Description: Set on England's Southwest coast, the story follows a father-son pair of struggling fishermen, John Winter and Charlie. A huge loss in their lives leads to a confrontation with emotions neither are equipped to deal with.

Title: Basma
Description: A young Saudi woman studying abroad returns to Jeddah, where she learns that her family has been shielding her from difficult truths.

Title: The Witness
Description: After seeing a government official commit murder in Iran, retired dance instructor Tarlan faces a choice: stay quiet under political pressure or risk everything to expose the truth.

Title: In Her Likeness
Description: A therapist's nightmares become intertwined with a patient's experiences. As her dreams intensify, she struggles to maintain boundaries between her work and personal life, uncovering a mysterious connection to her client.

Title: The Bodyguard
Description: Former special police sniper Zhong Xiaonan was hired by security company Gao Bin to protect the son of Chinese scientist Lin Heng, Lin Zihao, from returning to China. The scientific research achievements mastered by the Lin father and son have aroused the covetousness of overseas tycoons. They sent a killer group to try to kidnap Lin Zihao and steal core data, and even colluded with local police officials to launch a heavy siege on Zhong Xiaonan and Lin Zihao. In danger, Zhong Xiaonan teamed up with Chinese police officer Peter and resolutely decided to fight against evil forces to the end, and overthrow all "black evil".

Title: Die Ironie des Lebens
Description: Follow the life of Edgar, a successful comedian in his late 60s. But his offstage life is filled with loneliness, sadness, and the solace he finds in alcohol and groupies.

Title: Uno
Description: Esmeralda (Marcela Mar), a woman determined to uncover the truth behind the tragedy that destroyed her family, embarks on a desperate quest that leads her to unearth the darkest secrets of La Alameda, a small mining community in Colombia. With the help of Joaquín (Juan Pablo Urrego), a farmer who knows the land and its dangers well, she follows the last traces of her late husband, a high executive at a multinational mining company. Together, they slowly peel back the layers of something much more sinister and discover an ambitious society fighting for gold and territory. Esmeralda becomes trapped in a dangerous game of betrayal and power, where every step she takes brings her closer to the truth... but also to death.

Title: Unexposed
Description: After her marriage ends due to infidelity, Tracey Miller becomes a sleuth for cheating spouses, facing danger as she uncovers threats to her family.

Title: The Sky Above Zenica
Description: In the center of Europe, one of the worlds most polluted cities has united its citizens in a common fight for a viable future. But money, power and politics prove to be as toxic an opponent as the pollution that is threatening their lives.

Title: Blood, Beach, Betrayal
Description: At a high end beach club, a female college lifeguard gets caught up in a secret affair with a wealthy housewife.

Title: Saturn
Description: When a mysterious planet appears in the sky, a young father must choose between the life he loves and an ancient call to save the world.

Title: The Invasion
Description: Sergei Loznitsa questions the consequences of the invasion of one country by another.

Title: The Accidental Twins
Description: Two sets of identical twins switched at birth in Colombia explore their complex history and new identities in this captivating documentary.

Title: Ludzie
Description: Stories about the unintentional heroism that war forces people to do. A terrifying picture of the Russian invasion seen through the eyes of Ukrainian women who, in order to save themselves and their loved ones.

Title: Neelan & Kevin
Description: Neelan and Kevin are two brothers who get in over their heads after losing their mother's prized Tupperware to a local gang. Their mission to retrieve it leads to chaos, laughter and action in this uniquely South African action comedy.

Title: Members Club
Description: Wet Dreams, a middle aged male stripper group, take one last gig at a rural working mens club only to discover they are to become sacrifices in a plot to raise a murderous 16th century witch from the dead.

Title: C.D: Criminal or Devil
Description: Sidhu meets a girl named Raksha in an unexpected situation. Strangely, Raksha sometimes behaves like a devil and sometimes like a criminal. Is Raksha criminal or devil?

Title: Don't Look Back... I Know Your Origins
Description: The film tells the story of the long-time Opah's Saka looking for a new victim to tie up. However, there are obstacles and mysteries that cause various horrific incidents to occur.

Title: Karkhanu
Description: Three carpenters trapped in a haunted factory on Kalichaudash must burn a possessed girl's anklets, only to reveal the entire spooky tale was filmed in a single take with hilarious behind-the-scenes chaos.

Title: All Hallows' Eve: Inferno
Description: From an executive producer of Terrifier 2 comes All Hallows Eve: Inferno, a new installment of the franchise that first introduced the world to Damien Leone's Art the Clown and the short film Terrifier.

Title: Snake Skin Beauty
Description: In a town plagued by serial murders, corpse stitcher Li Nian resurrects a hydra, Xiao Mei, by stitching a headless corpse. She manipulates Li Nian's affections, seducing him to merge their love, while framing his wife as a demon snake.

Title: Shannon Matthews the Musical the Movie
Description: In this true-crime bad taste comedy singalong, Mother-from-hell Karen Matthews revels in her newfound fame, while everyone else searches for her missing daughter, little Shannon Matthews, aged 9.

Title: Booty Warrior
Description: Go Behind Bars with Fleece Johnson: Prison's Most Infamous Predator. Through his own words, Fleece recounts his time in prison, where survival often meant exploiting others.

Title: Juliette au printemps
Description: A woman who returns to her hometown to spend time with her family as buried memories, unspoken truths and long-buried secrets bubble up to the surface

Title: Fight Like a Girl
Description: A young Congolese woman forced to work in an illegal mineral mine, escapes her captors and finds a new life for herself as a professional boxer. Based on true events.

Title: Parents for Christmas
Description: Two orphan girls' wish for parents remains unfulfilled. A troubled child joins them at the children's home. The director takes them on a farm visit to lift their spirits during the holidays, hoping to bring joy amidst their struggles.

Title: Kontra
Description: Fanny has just moved from the suburbs to a new school in northern Copenhagen. She finds it difficult to adjust to the new environment, and a group of girls in her class seem to dominate the entire school. Fanny befriends the former leader of the group, Lilja, to form an alliance and do whatever it takes to become popular, have the same opportunities and get into the right circles. But the power struggle has a price, and what is the point of being popular if you don't even have a friend you can trust?

Title: Ognivo
Description: In a fairy-tale kingdom, a soldier on his way home accidentally finds a magic flint and frees the little girl Dasha, who was kidnapped and bewitched by the evil Likhodey, who was locked in it. To dispel his spell, the soldier will have to go on a dangerous journey.

Title: Demons at Dawn
Description: As the boys go against a diverse, ever-changing, hostile world, they'll learn that once the darkness of night is gone and through their intertwined bodies and their synchronized souls, they will have seen all those demons of dawn go by.

Title: Poison Sangga: The Homewrecker's Curse
Description: The life of a married couple, Maya and Andi, who both begin to be disturbed by a series of mysterious oddities.

Title: Varshangalkku Shesham
Description: The story of two friends set in two different time periods. Two boys, Murali and Venu, hailing from northern Kerala meet coincidentally and become friends.

Title: Sharmajee Ki Beti
Description: Multi-generational ensemble about the modern, middle-class female experience and the lives of urban women, all with the common surname of Sharma.

Title: Ma Este Gyilkolunk
Description: A former star of a crime TV series is forced to take on the role of a detective when a murder disguised as an accident occurs at the nursing home he has just moved into.

Title: Stealing Jokes
Description: Comedian Jake Burman and friends head out on tour. After getting stiffed for their pay on their first gig they rob the venue which sets the stage for a hilarious Ocean's Eleven type ride through the comedy underworld.

Title: Manas
Description: Aware that the future does not hold many options for her in a riverside community on Marajó Island, 13-year-old Marcielle decides to confront the violent machinery that governs her family and the women in her community.

Title: Silver Star
Description: Plot details kept under wraps.

Title: Planet 7693
Description: Luka, an imaginative nine year old boy tries to heal the disrupted family relations with the special help of his strange and mysterious friend 7693.

Title: Kevin James: Irregardless
Description: Kevin James stand-up comedy special with topics including parenting, marriage, and getting older.

Title: Transamazonia
Description: Rebecca is a girl healer whose fame attracts flocks to her father Lawrence Byrne's mission deep in the Amazon jungle. Rebecca and Byrne are dragged into an escalating conflict.

Title: Wrooklyn Zoo
Description: A new version of William Shakespeare's classic "Romeo and Juliet" in which Romeo, an expert skater, is enthralled by Julia, a Roma girl who seeks freedom from her background.

Title: Il corpo
Description: A night watchman escapes from the morgue where he works and is run over. The inspector called to investigate discovers that the body of a recently deceased woman is missing. Questioning the widower, he begins to suspect him.

Title: Mutant
Description: In 2150, artificial intelligence mutated and replaced humans control of the earth, and launched an eradication operation against humans. The surviving humans fought a desperate battle with the artificial intelligence army.

Title: Sometimes I Dream in Farsi
Description: After remembering a traumatic racist incident in his childhood, Pirooz Kalayeh decides to document his journey to recovery, traveling back to the barbershop where he was refused a haircut as a child, and then doing a series of role-plays with family, friends, and children to understand how racism leaves lasting effects and how he and others can heal and move forward.

Title: Tous toqués !
Description: A chef is enlisted to help a young girl win a culinary competition.

Title: SUGA: Agust D Tour 'D-DAY' the Movie
Description: A film of the encore concert by Agust D, also known as SUGA of BTS. Tune in to relive the moments from the concert encompassing his rich musical world and performances, explosive energy, and joint performance.

Title: Day Labor
Description: A Latino American veteran who seeks work as a day laborer in order to keep his family afloat. A regular day turns into a deadly game of survival when he is mistakenly dropped off at a private ranch in El Paso, Texas to be hunted for sport.

Title: The Diary of West Bengal
Description: Centred around the illegal influx of Rohingya Muslims and Bangladeshis extremist communities in the state and how the settlement of the Rohingyas and Bangladeshi infiltrators is being facilitated by the state government.

Title: UmroAyyar - A New Beginning
Description: UmroAyyar: A New Beginning is a 2024 Pakistani sci-fi film, based on the classical Urdu-Persian novel, Hamzanama's character, Umro Ayyar, a thief and legend warrior of Tilism-e-Hoshruba.

Title: Efsane
Description: There is a legend about a yoghurt recipe passed down from father to son. Since this does not happen, the family suffers a curse. An attempt is made to decide who among the twins deserves to learn the knowledge of the legend more.

Title: Krishnam Pranaya Sakhi
Description: A wealthy tycoon's son becomes a valet to win the heart of a girl from a humble background. Determined to marry her, he faces challenges in gaining approval from her parents.

Title: Pacific Fear
Description: Follows a group of surfers looking out for waves in a mysterious island that's been vanished from all maps.

Title: Krispy Rishtey
Description: Karan leaves Natasha to fulfill his father's dying wish. Married to Anjali, he lacks connection, desiring freedom from this arranged marriage. His path forward remains uncertain.

Title: Migraine
Description: An artist believes her headaches could be connected to a mysterious disappearance.

Title: Ghudchadi
Description: A middle-class father-son duo from Delhi in which a son-loving father doesn't want his son to get married with the love of his life and a father-loving son doesn't want his 60-year-old father to get married.

Title: Yalakunni
Description: In a village, cruel rich man Nagappa oppresses locals who unite and kill him. His orphaned son lives among them, seeking revenge but eventually sacrificing himself for their sake.

Title: Trifole
Description: In this bittersweet portrait of a vanishing rural way of life, Dalia travels to Piedmont to care for her aging grandfather Igor, an expert forager. Armed with his loyal dog Birba, she hunts for a prizewinning truffle to save his home.

Title: Concussed: The American Dream
Description: Tyler Sash was drafted by the New York Giants and became a part of the 2012 Super Bowl winning team. Concussions would cut Sash's career short and the film is paralleled by NFL Hall of Famer Brett Favre's CTE experience.

Title: Nawi
Description: 13-year-old Nawi finds out her father is selling her to a much older man for a herd of goats. Instead of obeying tradition she chooses to fight her impending marriage and embarks on a journey to reclaim her dream of joining high school.

Title: Soodhu Kavvum 2: Naatum Naatu Makkalum
Description: A gang of kidnappers find they have bitten off more than they can chew.

Title: Rose Rosy Te Gulab
Description: Gulab, discontented with his single life, embarks on a manifestation journey advised by friends, finding himself torn between Rose and Rosy. His choice will determine his romantic future.

Title: Star
Description: Follows a youngster Kalai and his aspirations of becoming a 'Star' in the Tamil Film Industry. Born in a lower-middle-class family, will Kalai overcome all his struggles to emerge as a Star?

Title: Vegan
Description: A vegan social media influencer goes on a quest to document the search for her biological parents. Her search leads her to a defunct, secluded farm where she encounters The Farmer, and her worst nightmares become reality.

Title: Could Have Waited for August
Description: Xavier, a village boy, falls for Laura, neighbor's granddaughter who visits her grandfather annually. Despite flirting at summer dances, Xavier believes he has no chance with her.

Title: The Ultimate Stack
Description: Documentary focused on the 2023 WPT Championship with the aim of showing a poker tournament from the beginning to the end through the eyes of the chips. Beginning with one player we will continue to follow the opponent that eliminates them until the eventual winner of the tournament. We will take the viewer on the roller coaster ride we call tournament poker and educate those who are unfamiliar.

Title: Time Passages
Description: A filmmaker "time travels" via his family archive as his mother's health declines from dementia, racing against the clock to resolve his fraught relationship to family and nation when COVID strikes her nursing home.

Title: Sinhabahu
Description: The movie is based on the legend of King Sinhabahu, the son of a lion and a royal princess Suppa Devi.

Title: Polar
Description: A police officer from a Homicide Group is fired because of her problems with alcohol and drugs that she has had since her son died.

Title: Alice: On & Off
Description: Filmed over ten years, this is the story of Alice, an unloved girl trapped in a young mother's life. At 16, she falls in love with Dorian, 35 years her senior.

Title: Dasama
Description: Follows a close circle of friends in a tiny village school. It seamlessly flashes between their past and present, highlighting the camaraderie and enthusiasm of their adolescence.

Title: Dinner with Leatherface
Description: Documentary about Gunnar Hansen, the actor who portrayed Leatherface in "The Texas Chainsaw Massacre" (1974). Friends, colleagues, filmmakers, and fellow actors share personal stories and discuss the dichotomy between the maniacal chainsaw-wielding character he played on-screen and the very intelligent, creative, soft-spoken man he actually was in real life.

Title: I Miss You
Description: College sweethearts Bai and Jin Jin reunite after graduation. Despite differing backgrounds, they fall in love but face obstacles to marriage. The story follows their journey to overcome challenges and stay together.

Title: The French Italian
Description: Neighbors prank each other, situation escalates comically amid NYC apartment complex's cutthroat politics, exploring absurdity of conflict between residents.

Title: Indrani: Epic-1 Dharam vs Karam
Description: In 2122 AD when world faces an imminent problem from a rogue nation, Indrani working for Indian Super Force (ISF) has to travel in time to past to find the solution for it. Story revolves around the emotional journey of Indrani.

Title: Moneyslapper
Description: In dreary Porac Pampanga, a young man, Daniel (John Lloyd Cruz), abandons his motherland after winning the biggest cash prize in the history of Philippine lottery. Five years later, he is searching for home and redemption through the people that make up his past. With each visit, his story unfolds like the last digit of a winning combination.

Title: Jin Qian Bao Lei
Description: While investigating a stock fraud case involving tens of billions of yuan, Zheng Yi, the captain of the Economic Investigation Team, discovered that Han Dongchuan used live broadcasting to induce investment and commit fraud.

Title: Off the Line
Description: "Mark Stevenson, a determined young inline speedskater, is eager to establish himself in the sport. Upon learning that the circuit will finance and send a race team to race the prestigious European Grand Prix 24-hour race to beat the circuits biggest rivals Tropen Racing. Mark Stevenson and his friend Jake Flyer embark on a journey of rigorous training and seek out a seasoned coach who is struggling with life. Their aim is not only to win the race but also to bring order to their lives. Amidst the backdrop of business, sports, romance, and adventure, the narrative delves into the intricate world of inline speed skating"

Title: When Fucking Spring is in the Air
Description: It is a feel-good road movie about 17-year-old rebellious Kasia, and her worthless family.

Title: Warning 2
Description: Geja fails to assassinate Pamma and ends up in the same jail, where he's intent on finishing the job. A merciless cop's plan to transfer the dangerous prisoners escalates the situation.

Title: Hold Me Close
Description: Seven years after traveling worldwide, Woody lands in Japan, encountering Lynlyn, gifted to sense individuals' potential impact on her life through touch.

Title: Perdiendo el Juicio
Description: A legal case unites two lawyers between rivalry and romance.

Title: Public Defender
Description: Follows the work of Heather Shaner, a lawyer representing January 6th rioters, who works to confront America's political divisions with empathy.

Title: Indelebile
Description: Veronica, a 16-year-old girl, is spending the Christmas holidays at her grandfather's in a small village in the Sicilian hinterland when a woman disappears and the fear of the monster who had sown terror in the area ten years earlier returns. The girl suddenly begins to feed a terrible suspicion: her own grandfather could be the culprit.

Title: Caracas
Description: A well-known Neapolitan writer returns to his hometown after a long absence and encounters an old friend known as Caracas. Caracas, once a neo-fascist skinhead, is now converting to Islam.

Title: Beware the Boogeyman
Description: For her first day of orientation, Dr. Tristian Mackenzie makes her way to the Silverdale Psychiatric Hospital for the criminally insane, where she learns of the strange series of cases from the similarly strange Dr. Moon.

Title: Measures for a Funeral
Description: Young academic pursues acclaimed early 20th-century Canadian violinist Kathleen Parlow while escaping her failed musician mother's shadow in this poignant character study.

Title: In Waves and War
Description: Highly decorated Navy SEAL Marcus Capone struggles with PTSD after returning from Afghanistan. His wife finds hope in psychedelic therapy. They embark on providing access to this treatment for other veterans battling mental health issues.

Title: Four.
Description: A small-town couple with big dreams of making their family complete must persevere through infertility and tragedy

Title: Package Deal
Description: A newlywed couple's life takes an unexpected turn when an uninvited guest arrives.

Title: Renee Gracie: Fireproof
Description: Australia's first female V8-Star Renee Gracie attempts to re-enter racing after being pushed out of the sport and becoming Australia's top earner on OnlyFans.

Title: Gulaabi
Description: "Celebrating the Colors of Friendship"

Title: Uang Panai' 2 Maha(r)l
Description: Iccang loves Icha, a beautiful woman from a prominent family who asks for a large amount of dowry.

Title: Tati Part Time
Description: A lawyer willing to compromise for his career, must care for Maya, his 8-year-old goddaughter. Their orderly lives are disrupted as he adjusts to parenthood and she to her new guardian.

Title: Hide and Seek
Description: A police officer is on a trail to hunt an elusive Ghost Leader indulged in trafficking.When an order for a wealthy businessman's daughters is given, the hero takes the job, but it leads to unexpected twists and turns.

Title: Gold Raiders
Description: Sisters search for Blackbeard's lost treasure, racing against ruthless rivals who'll stop at nothing, including murder, to claim the legendary pirate gold before them.

Title: I Win
Description: While doing community service, Jax Donovan meets a young man with Down Syndrome. He also befriends Bailey, and Juliette, and they forge a friendship that teaches them about love, life and forgiveness.

Title: Janji Darah
Description: Two people who once tied a promise to each other, face a very impossible problem after death separates them, because their promise is to always protect each other wherever they are.

Title: Le choix du pianiste
Description: A talented French pianist faces an impossible choice during wartime: perform for Nazi officers or lose the woman he loves - his former mentor who taught him everything he knows.

Title: To Kill a Wolf
Description: In a modern re-imagining of Little Red Riding Hood, a social pariah discovers a teenage runaway in the Oregon Wilderness and does his best to help her find a way home - a troubling exploration of trauma and redemption.

Title: House of Lies
Description: After Albert's murder on his birthday, Officer Rajeev investigates numerous suspects, uncovering lies and seeking the mastermind behind the seemingly perfect Pinto House.

Title: Easter Bloody Easter
Description: A woman must protect her small town from the Jackalope and his army of devilish bunnies as they embark on a murder spree over the Easter weekend.

Title: Lineman
Description: In Chandakavadi village, Nata, a lineman, refuses to provide power for a celebration honoring midwife Shardamma's 100th birthday.

Title: Only Andy
Description: Adult worker, Andy Lee, and his co-workers share their own insightful and interesting perspectives on the adult industry, in a bid to shed some light on the frequently misunderstood adult industry.

Title: Pavi Caretaker
Description: An unmarried caretaker's life changes when he forms an unexpected bond, adding joy to his routine existence in a residential complex amidst life's challenges.

Title: The Aegean
Description: A widowed Greek fisherman and a teenage refugee form an emotional bond while sailing the azure waters of the Aegean Sea.

Title: Parakramam
Description: Revolves around the life of Lovaraju, a theatre artist and a gully cricketer in a village named Lampakalova.

Title: Isla Monstro
Description: When loser Duke, who has screwed up every hair-brained scheme he's ever come up with, accidentally falls off a cruise ship and wakes up on a mysterious top secret government island, he discovers that it's overrun with mutants and monsters from a failed 1980s DARPA "super soldier" project to stop the 2nd Cold War. He soon comes up with the incredible idea of turning the island into a world class getaway resort, utilizing the creatures as it's staff, much to the dismay of the United States government.

Title: Scotoe
Description: Steetwise detectives Sino and Mo are the first to track down a major cocaine smuggling operation. They try to solve the case with their unique Turkish and Moroccan investigative methods.

Title: Swag
Description: Follows the swaganika bloodline which changes the matriarchal society to patriarchal society.

Title: Snow White
Description: Looking for love on dating apps. Iman falls for the romantic Emad online, she hides her dwarfism using a filter and catfishes Emad, but for the sake of love. Will her little secret be forgiven?

Title: My New Friends
Description: Lucie, a police officer, is fond of her new neighbors, a young couple. Soon she discovers that Yann, the father, has a heavy criminal record. Lucie has a moral conflict between her professionalism and her desire to help this family.

Title: Final Wager
Description: Former sports gambling addict, Chance needs $60,000 to save his mother from nursing home eviction. So he falls back into his old habits, only to learn he's never lost a bet on Christmas. Is this the Christmas miracle he's been waiting for? Or just an addict who can't control himself?

Title: Superman Reborn
Description: For the first time ever, a live script reading performance of the never before seen first draft of the unmade 5th Christopher Reeve Superman movie.

Title: Mala persona
Description: A man appreciated by everyone decides to start behaving badly with his loved ones when he receives the news that he has little time left to live.

Title: Team of Two
Description: When facing the most dangerous criminal is easier than facing your new partner

Title: Major Grom: The Game
Description: A year has passed since the defeat of the Plague Doctor, and Igor Grom has become a hero for the whole city. But now he is waiting for a fight with a new supervillain.

Title: Dosen Ghaib: It's Nighttime or You Already Know
Description: Four students had to take a short semester while other students were on holiday. At first these students were not suspicious during class.

Title: Russians at War
Description: A Russian-Canadian filmmaker gains unprecedented access to follow a Russian Army battalion in Ukraine.

Title: Midas
Description: After a charismatic college dropout lies his way into a job at an insurance juggernaut, he recruits his two best friends for a plot to steal thousands. In the process, they uncover a much darker scheme that tests the limits of their greed.

Title: Heartbreak Motel
Description: At a quiet motel, a rising star in the film industry must confront her past as she navigates her flourishing career and delicate personal relationships.

Title: Sam and Colby: The Legends of the Paranormal
Description: Paranormal investigators Sam and Colby have hunted ghosts at the world's most iconic haunted locations. Now they set out to investigate a mysterious desert ranch famous for ghosts, UFOs, and terrifying monsters lurking in the dark.

Title: Farki Farki
Description: Based on a time 'infinite time loop' theory, a light hearted romantic comedy that showcases various aspects of our lives.

Title: Bremenskie muzykanty
Description: The troubadour and his impostor friends - a Dog, a Cat, a Donkey and a narcissistic Rooster - teamed up to accomplish the feat. The wandering musicians, led by a new leader, will rally again to bring laughter and joy back to the gloomy streets of Bremen. First of all, they must make the King's daughter laugh, but meeting the Princess threatens a dangerous adventure. There are insidious enemies, intrigues and traps against the Troubadour and his friends, but you have to fight for love. And then the Princess ran away from the palace. In one tangle there are criminal schemes of Robbers, intrigues of a Detective, whims and secrets of the royal family, but cheerful musicians with an indefatigable Troubadour will make everyone dance to their tune. What are the Bremen Town musicians willing to do for the sake of the feat?

Title: He Sees You When You're Sleeping
Description: Chester returns to his home after witnessing his parents' murders 17 years ago by a killer dressed as Santa. A new Santa killer begins killing his relatives. Chester questions if the killer returned or if a more terrifying truth exists.

Title: Spirit Riser
Description: Two sisters are thrown out of their isolation and onto opposite coasts of America by a terrifying cosmic entity. On their quest to reunite they discover their own supernatural abilities and meet many strange characters.

Title: A Girl Named Ann
Description: A drug-addicted girl from an abusive family finds hope through kind people but her grim reality strikes back just as she sees a glimmer of light.

Title: Kai Jones' Falling into Place
Description: Kai Jones, born into Teton Gravity Research, turned pro at 12, gaining fame with viral videos and Skier of the Year nods. At 16, a near-fatal injury tested his resilience in this raw, inspiring journey.

Title: Water Horse
Description: A paranormal investigator links a bizarre string of seemingly unrelated events to the disappearance of her mother.

Title: Something's More Than One Thing
Description: A young couple go down a rabbit hole of conflicting internet advice in order to save their relationship.

Title: Panopticon
Description: Hen Sandro's father decides to devote his existence to God and leaves for a monastery, the teenage introvert finds himself deprived of the fundamental certainties of life. Abandoned by his father and his mother, who is working abroad, the young man embarks on a journey of self-discovery, opening up both to a new friendship with the radical Lasha, who has ties with an ultra-right organisation, and also to the chance to explore his own sexuality. George Sikharulidze's perceptive feature debut considers how fine the line is between the observer and the observed, and asks where contemporary post-Soviet Georgian society is heading as it hovers on the border between religious conservatism and nationalisation on the one hand, and the desire for independence and modernisation on the other.

Title: The Rubber-Keyed Wonder
Description: Sinclair ZX Spectrum. This film goes into all the finer details of how and why the ZX Spectrum was created, what impact the computer had as well as the various versions

Title: Horror Able
Description: A documentary about creatives with disabilities within the horror industry.

Title: Poppay Ki Wedding
Description: A modern era boy visits hometown for his sister's wedding, soon discovering his own proposal finalized with a girl he's never seen. Fighting against the family customs, his only mission is to at least see the face of his future wife-to-be.

Title: No Voltees
Description: When two siblings return to their childhood home, they are confronted by a violent, supernatural presence that dwells deep within their worst traumas.

Title: El instinto
Description: A home invasion thriller starring a dog trainer trying to modify a human's brain.

Title: Clown II
Description: A troubled young woman moves to a small town to start fresh with her aunt, but soon learns the locals have a vendetta against her family-and her past might be the key to unraveling their dangerous secrets.

Title: Stinky Summer
Description: Join Olivia and friends plus a lovable skunk at Camp Clover as they outsmart international spies from stealing her dad's secret invention in a wild summer adventure.

Title: Checkmate
Description: A former international secret agent must put together his old team for a desperate new mission when his niece is kidnapped.

Title: BeBe Winans' We Three Kings
Description: Retired musician Lincoln, a record store owner and father to estranged sisters Lydia, Gracie, and Abigail, conspires with friend Genelle to reunite them for Christmas after their mother's passing.

Title: Una storia nera
Description: Carla, a mother of three, endured twenty years of abuse from her husband, is arrested for premeditated murder, though she claims selfdefense.

Title: The Temp
Description: When an attorney's trusted secretary goes on maternity leave, he turns to a temp agency for a replacement. Enter Erica, a mysterious and captivating woman whose arrival brings a deadly turn to the attorney and his wife.

Title: Boonie Bears: Time Twist
Description: When Vick gets a chance to start his life again as a logger, he must save his friends by embarking on an adventure through time and space.

Title: Gharat Ganpati
Description: Amidst Konkan's stunning landscape, the Gharat Family cherishes welcoming Gauri Ganpati into their ancestral home during the Ganpati festival. Spanning generations, this rich tradition fosters a poignant reunion navigating complexities.

Title: Quadrant
Description: Quadrant helmet transports users' minds into nightmarish AI worlds. A girl becomes Jack the Ripper, unleashing terror in virtual London and reality. A vicious killer enters the Quadrant-verse to stop her in a brutal battle across worlds.

Title: La Femme cachée
Description: Haunted by a past she hoped to escape, pregnant Halima reluctantly allows her partner Sylvain to join her in the pursuit of her estranged family abroad.

Title: Bir Cumhuriyet Sarkisi
Description: In 1930s Turkey, a handful of young, talented and determined people strive to realize an artistic revolution in a fledgling country.

Title: Love Over Money
Description: Love Over Money tells the incredible true story of John Robbins, heir apparent to the Baskin-Robbins ice cream empire, who turns down a billion-dollar inheritance from his father to follow his own truth.

Title: Texas Twister
Description: A small town worker believes he's seeing visions from God in the form of a violent tornado.

Title: G for Gap
Description: Wudi returns to hometown after career/love setbacks, disrupting family life. Forced cohabitation, he explores new paths. Meeting old classmate Feng Liuliu unexpectedly alters his trajectory amid rejections.

Title: Punishment
Description: Four inmates on maximum security have chosen to enter a three-week Jesuit silent retreat in prison. They are guided by two priests. The film slowly observes this paradoxical situation, while looking beyond the question of religious belief: How does ethical exercises, rituals and communal silence affect us? The setting evolves into a prism for gauging a portrait of the existential landscape of the convicted.

Title: Sei fratelli
Description: Marco, Guido, Leo, Luisa, Gaelle, and Mattia have different mothers. They are not all biological children of the same father but have one true father figure of reference: Manfredi Alicante. When the latter passes away, they all find themselves together for the first time in their father's house in Bordeaux, experiencing the illusion that they can become a united family. However, by now each of them carries with them a history, an identity, and going back will not be easy.

Title: Persona
Description: A Man forms a passionate and sensual relationship with a woman in his dreams, upon waking up he must deceive his surreal hallucinations and Insomnia to find a way to re-unite with her again.

Title: Babymetal: Legend 43 - The Movie
Description: Japanese Metal Band BABYMETAL's Concert film which took place in Okinawa,as a finale of their BABYMETAL WORLD TOUR 2023-2024 at March 24, 2024.

Title: Resynator
Description: When her genius inventor father dies, a daughter finds his old synth prototype, sparking a quest to learn his secrets and forge a posthumous connection.

Title: New Wave
Description: Exploring the defiant Vietnamese new wave music scene, a filmmaker takes a vulnerable, personal look at her community revisiting their unexamined past.

Title: Remember I am Dead
Description: A young farmer of 31 years, Sagat, heads to a cemetery in the middle of the night. The next morning, Roman, a 29-year-old guy, is found sitting in Sagat's living room. It seems he has never been in that place before. Yet, something suggests otherwise. Who is he? What ties them together? Why is he there, and for how long?

Title: Inverted
Description: An off-the-grid satanic cult known as "The Inverts" kidnap a group of diverse individuals to recruit for the Holy War against the second coming of Christ.

Title: Eros
Description: This explores the architectures of sex, love and intimacy through one of Brazil's most adored and infamous institutions: The Motel. The footage provide a unique insight into the sexual and emotional psyche of a nation.

Title: Aakhir Palaayan Kab Tak..?
Description: A cop faces personal struggles in a deceptive town where dark forces exploit community sentiments. The movie explores themes of greed, community manipulation, and personal redemption.

In a post-apocalyptic universe, clans compete to acquire the last stocks of Ridex, an antidote allowing survival after a virus has decimated life on Earth. Between stalking and betrayals, the fate of Mankind rests on a few chosen by God.

Title: Tiny Lights
Description: Six-year-old Amálka is shut out of a family argument. She spends an idyllic afternoon at the lake with her grandparents and later learns the fuss was about her mother's plan to break away and live as an artist in Prague.

Title: Dream Team
Description: In this absurdist homage to 90's basic cable TV thrillers, two hot INTERPOL agents uncover an international, interspecies mystery. A post-modern, soft-core fever dream.

Title: Patna Shukla
Description: Tanvi Shukla, a lawyer in Patna's lower court, who is living her childhood dream of becoming a lawyer.

Title: Go for Broke
Description: Zhang Yao, whose family was destroyed by drug dealers, secretly cooperates with Anti-drug team leader An Du. The two join forces to ruthlessly eliminate the evil and vow to wipe out Mukun and Anpei, the Top 2 figures of the criminal group.

Title: Bangkok Dog
Description: The story focuses on an American agent sent to a dangerous undercover mission in Thailand to dismantle a sadistic crime lord.

Title: Paluwagan
Description: In a province where most housewives are deprived of intimacy by their busy husbands, a new savings cooperative is introduced by a merchant. The salary to claim: cash or a night with a mysterious man. The women surely know what to choose.

Title: Maria's Silence
Description: The story of Maria Leiko - a famous actress who late in her career has to decide between fame and love for her grandchild, between her ideals or the lies of Stalin's totalitarian regime.

Title: Don't Make a Sound
Description: When their car breaks down in the woods, two sisters become the hunted prey of a deranged killer, who captures his victims on film.

Title: The Ghost
Description: Éamon and his daughter Máire, are employed as caretakers for an isolated Georgian Mansion during the harsh winter months. Little do they know that this seemingly peaceful assignment will unleash a nightmare upon them.

Title: Any Other Way: The Jackie Shane Story
Description: Jackie Shane was one of music's pioneering Black trans performers. On the edge of stardom, why did she disappear? Any Other Way: The Jackie Shane Story hands the mic over revealing her extraordinary journey, in her own unmistakable voice.

Title: Døde menn går på ski
Description: A billionaire invites a failed writer, a misogynistic psychiatrist, a cocaine-sniffing children's TV star, and a psychotic journalist to a haunted cabin for Easter. A thrilling detective game turns deadly when one is found beheaded. Trapped by a snowstorm, they are forced expose the murderer among them, before it is too late. Based on Knut Nærums bestseller.

Title: Teacher's Pet
Description: When a dog wants to be a boy after watching Pinocchio, he meets a mad scientist who steals his mind. Now his owner, a lizard, and a parrot have to go into the timelines to give him pizza and save him.

Title: Escanyapobres
Description: Late 1800s. The arrival of the railroad to an isolated town brings the long-awaited progress, but also Oleguer, a dark loan shark with shady dealings. When he seizes and stays at Cileta and her family's farmhouse, the young peasant will do anything possible to get her house back. Even if that means following in the dark footsteps of the money-lender.

Title: I Hate Love
Description: Ramababu hates love for a certain reason but dramatically he loves Sita. Sita's father knows that his daughter's life will be fruitful if marries her to Rambabu but he refuses their union.

Title: Best Man Dead Man
Description: A bachelor party in the middle of nowhere quickly turns into a night of murder and mystery when the best man ends up with a knife in his head. Everyone is a suspect and only an eccentric private eye in town can solve the mystery.

Title: Klaus & Barroso
Description: A bartender-combiner urgently needs to pay off a debt. He persuades his brother, a fiery bouncer, to arrange a bachelor party together, without the knowledge of the owners of the club where he works.

Title: The Jury: Murder Trial
Description: How much can we trust our justice system? This landmark experiment follows the restaging of a real-life murder trial in front of two juries of ordinary people. Will they reach the same verdict? Shown over 4 Consequtive Days.

Title: Scrambled
Description: 'Scrambled' follows the uniquely quirky story of a man with half a penis, freshly out of prison, as he reenters the his former best friend's life, who is now an omelette chef, and wreaks havoc in all aspects of his life.

Title: Double Engine
Description: Danny and friends seek a mythic two-headed serpent, finding camaraderie and self-discovery during their fanciful quest.

Title: Plastic Guns
Description: During a trip to Denmark, a man is arrested and accused of murdering his wife and three children. Though maintaining his innocence, he remains jailed as police investigate.

Title: Beyond the Gaze: Jule Campbell's Swimsuit Issue
Description: Jule Campbell's 32-year reign as editor of Sports Illustrated's Swimsuit Issue, transforming it into a media empire. Exploring changing beauty standards, feminism's evolution, and interviews with Campbell and supermodels she championed.

Title: Mother Maker Lover Taker
Description: A young woman finds a way to resurrect the lover she lost to suicide, with devastating, unforeseen consequences.

Title: 2 Fingers Honey 2
Description: The sequel to the movie "2 Fingers Honey" by Ermal Mamaqi. The adventures of the newly married couple continue. This time, they leave for a family vacation to Turkey but mix up their plane tickets and end up at the wrong airport.

Title: Amar Prem Ki Prem Kahani
Description: Amar and Prem, along with their families, gather in Punjab for their wedding, which is disrupted by cultural differences and a jealous woman.

Title: Veerayi Makkal
Description: A once close family of three brothers and a sister face growing divides and tensions but ultimately reunites through forgiveness after a tragedy strikes, reaffirming the strength of familial bonds.

Title: Dracula: The Count's Kin
Description: A century after his legendary death, Dracula's blood sister has emerged with her own nefarious plans. Will a newly minted private detective with a mysterious past put an end to these malevolent intentions?

Title: Üç Günlük Dünya
Description: Muhittin, who owns a monopoly in one of the slums of Istanbul, finds it difficult to make ends meet by producing his own alcohol.

Title: Fresh Off Markham
Description: In Markham, a Chinese immigrant and a small-time crook's attempt to rob a Japanese restaurant goes terribly wrong. Unsuspectingly taking up the two gangsters and an influencer in a carpool, a driver is entangled in a sinister predicament.

Title: Old World Order
Description: Our history has been fabricated. The official timeline of our recent past, does not match our reality. Our Rockefeller "his-story" books are pure fabrication. There has been a massive cover-up.

Title: DreadClub: Vampire's Verdict
Description: Betty Gray, a college student obsessed with gothic romances, finds herself living one when she falls for Duchamps De Ve--a man on trial for being a vampire.

Title: No Woman Is an Island
Description: An insightful sit down chat with five of Malta's influential female trailblazers, some of whom are artists, all of whom are paving the way for change.

Title: Opa Cor
Description: A law-abiding Rotterdam dock worker and proud grandfather.

Title: Silence of the Prey
Description: In a desperate bid to secure a future for her child, an undocumented immigrant mother takes a caretaker job. Unbeknownst to her, the elderly man conceals a horrifying truth.

Title: I Am the River, the River Is Me
Description: Māori tribal leader Ned Tapa takes a group of friends and family on a canoe trip down the Whanganui River in Aotearoa/New Zealand, the first river in the world recognized as a legal person.

Title: Tragic Awakening
Description: Explores antisemitism's roots, origins of Jewish hatred, and prospects for transforming it into a positive force through candid insights.

Title: Samandar
Description: Brothers Uday and Salman join fisheries mafia under ex-MLA Arjan Parmar. They target Imtiaz Memon, tied to Uday's sister's demise. Power struggle, betrayal, and politics strain their bond as revenge and fisheries mafia intersect.

Title: Arata Natsume's Marriage
Description: Arata Natsume is a former gangster, who now works as an employee at a child guidance center. One of the children under his care is a boy whose father was murdered by Shinju Shinagawa. Shinju committed a series of murders" She was sentenced to death for her crimes and, at the age of 22, awaits her punishment on death row. The head of the boy's father was never found, so the boy has exchanged letters with Shinju by using Arata's name as the pen name. The latest letter from Shinju asks to see Arata in person. The boy comes to Arataand asks him to meet Shinju in prison. Arata decides to grant the boy's wish and goes to meet her in prison, but he unexpectedly proposes to her to get married in prison. Arata begins to dig up the truth of the case.

Title: Vina: Before 7 Days
Description: Vina, a victim of a motorbike gang's atrocities in Cirebon, refuses to accept her death being labeled an accident. Her spirit intervenes within the seven days preceding the incident to reveal the truth behind what really happened.

Title: Married
Description: Two strangers meet through a ride-sharing app and find themselves sharing more than what's expected. Both having problems with their respective marital lives, they find comfort in each other's company.

Title: The Mediterranean
Description: Haia, who was pursuing her dream of pursuing a Masters degree in South Korea, almost failed after her scholarship was closed by the government.

Title: Hunt
Description: Follows Dr. Keerthy as he receives a case at a medical college that unfolds something that he was not expecting.

Title: Las super estrellas de la lucha libre
Description: The film tells the story of the wrestling gold era of Puerto Rico. From the beginning to the End.

Title: If Jack Reacher Could Sing
Description: Author Lee Child, known for his Jack Reacher series, always dreamed of writing songs with his favorite band, Naked Blue. He's about to get his chance.

Title: Tsunami Sharks
Description: A tsunami hits the city and soon, sharks begin infesting the waters..

Title: Ghost Killer
Description: After being possessed by the ghost of vengeful hit man Kudo, college student Fumika Matsuoka agrees to help him finish his quest for vengeance from beyond the grave.

Title: Sunshine
Description: It follows a young gymnast who discovers she is pregnant on the week of the national team tryouts. On her way to a seller of illegal abortion drugs, she meets a mysterious girl who eerily talks and thinks like her.

Title: The Legend Hunters
Description: The story follows the team as they try to raid a tomb made by master tomb raiders. It is set partially in Russia and will involve scenes at Catherine Palace in St. Petersburg.

Title: L'ultima settimana di settembre
Description: Pietro Rinaldi, an elderly writer, widower and tired of life, plans to commit suicide on his birthday. After the sudden and tragic death of his daughter and son-in-law, Pietro will have to look after his teenage nephew Mattia.

Title: Bach - Ein Weihnachtswunder
Description: 1734: Bach defies the Leipzig city council by rehearsing the Xmas Oratorio with his choir to prove he can enthrall the congregation. But the performance is canceled. Bach's wife Anna uses her connections to help change the council's edict.

Title: From Darkness to Light
Description: Explores Jerry Lewis' unreleased 1972 film "The Day The Clown Cried", its mysterious disappearance, and the search for footage. Includes interviews with Lewis' associates and previously unseen production content.

Title: Hunter of the Night
Description: When 5 friends accidentally stumble upon a man with a deranged PROMISE, they start to realize this college get away is a deadly trap. Is a rescue, really a rescue, if the PROMISE isn't kept. Be Frightened.

Title: Dr. Sander's Sleep Cure
Description: A man, plagued by insomnia, turns to Doctor Sander's Sleep Cure tapes for relief, becoming the unwitting star of his own nightmarish productions, navigating through bizarre and morbid dreamscapes filled with macabre humor.

Title: Without Warning
Description: A breath-takingly up-close view of the fury of the volcano

Title: El bus de la vida
Description: Andrés, a music teacher from Madrid, faints from cancer on his first day in Basque town, overcoming shared experiences and fears to reach Bilbao hospital.

Title: The Human Hibernation
Description: A woman wakes from hibernation while her brother sleeps on. The procedure makes humans seem animal-like. A sci-fi thought experiment portrayed in vivid scenes.

Title: Superkrachten voor je hoofd
Description: Lev, an insecure boy, leads a dull life with annoying parents who restrict him. However, everything changes when his cool, rebellious grandma shows up at his doorstep and sweeps him away on an exciting adventure to discover his own superpowers. The film "Superpowers for Your Mind" combines great adventures with important themes in mental resilience (including fear of failure, self-confidence, and positive thinking) and offers an inspiring story about courage, acceptance, and believing in oneself. Thanks to his fearless grandma and the challenges they face together, Lev learns to embrace his own shortcomings. He discovers that true superpower doesn't lie in the ability to fly, laser eyes, or controlling objects, but in his mind.

Title: Umjolo: Day Ones
Description: Childhood besties Zanele and Andile face a crossroads in their relationship. With Andile married and raising kids, Zanele grapples with the possibility that their bond might never evolve beyond friendship.

Title: Gary
Description: Explores Gary Coleman's rise to fame as a child star, his struggles with living in the spotlight, financial troubles, depression, and the controversy surrounding his tragic death at age 42, providing insight into his private world.

Title: Shakhahaari
Description: Centers on the unexpected intertwining of innocent lives leading to a murder mystery in a vegetarian restaurant run by Chef Subbanna.

Title: The Desperate Chase
Description: A detective partners with a con artist adept at disguises to take down a powerful criminal organization. Their unlikely alliance faces challenges as they navigate the dangerous underworld, uncovering secrets and confronting mafia's.

Title: Audrey
Description: The movie depicts the hope that blooms like petals in the trials faced by a mother and son who seem ordinary but are so special to each other.

Title: The Sintern
Description: A young woman hell-bent on revenge takes a job as an intern at a megachurch to expose a corrupt pastor's dark secrets.

Title: H.P. Lovecraft's the Shadow Over Innsmouth
Description: A history professor tracing his family tree visits the seaside town of Innsmouth, on the North Yorkshire coast. While there he becomes caught up in disturbing events that lead to horrifying personal revelations.

Title: River of Ghosts
Description: A psychiatry student returns to his hometown as a hypnotherapist. Treating townspeople's issues, he becomes popular but faces self-doubt until a challenging case arises, forcing him to confront his own demons for personal growth.

Title: Lost Angels
Description: A chilling supernatural thriller that follows a young artist (Agnes Born) who, amidst the echoing cries of a baby, finds her apartment consumed by an eerie and malevolent presence.

Title: The Falling Sky
Description: Documentary about Indigenous peoples' profound connection to nature and their struggle against deforestation, a grave threat to their way of life and the ecosystem they call home.

Title: August
Description: The documentary marks the directorial debut of Chinese actor Zhang Zhehan, it documents his deeply personal journey of self-healing in the aftermath of a devastating cyber media storm in August 2021 that abruptly halted his acting career.

Title: Swing Bout
Description: Set backstage at a major boxing event, a young boxer is plunged into a tumultuous journey from the dressing room to her ring walk in a night of deceit, betrayal, and life-altering decisions.

Title: Natatorium
Description: Visiting estranged grandparents, eighteen-year-old Lilja auditions in town. Feeling at home in their mansion, she becomes entangled with the family's dark past and learns life-threatening secrets.

Title: Petak Umpet
Description: A game of hide-and-seek by children in a haunted old house takes a horrific turn when one of them never returns after his turn to hide.

Title: Paint Me a Road Out of Here
Description: A wild tale of the painting's whitewashed journey and the two artists who challenge the same powerful, oppressive, and persistent institutions, a half-century apart with their artwork, their voices, and their shared persistent goals.

Title: The Last Sacrifice
Description: Interrogating true crime's cultural impact, from murderous origins to modern revival. Exposing British society's prejudices and dark underbelly.

Title: The Alexandrian
Description: In the heart of Alexandria, where Bakr Al-Iskandarani goes through many conflicts with his father, his cousin, and his lover. He travel abroad in search of a new life. when he returns after realizing himself, the conflicts return again.

Title: Letters at Christmas
Description: Amidst renovation of an old hotel, a divorcing couple's marriage gets a chance when their kids find love letters from the past. Saving their parents' marriage before a developer buys the hotel becomes the siblings' mission.

Title: Tekka
Description: A janitor who lost his job and is trying to get it back by holding a girl hostage. Things get complicated when the girl's mother, Pooja, kidnaps Iqlakh's son Guddu, creating a stalemate between the parents.

Title: Tracing the Divide
Description: Two lifelong friends test their limits and find new purpose as they ride the rigorous Great Divide Mountain Bike Route from Canada to Mexico.
